00:07:46,953 --> 00:07:48,052
- No, that's not it.
- No.

239
00:07:48,053 --> 00:07:49,192
- You two were too busy?
- That doesn't sound nice.

240
00:07:49,193 --> 00:07:51,162
We'll go there when Kyung Hoon is busy.

241
00:07:51,163 --> 00:07:52,292
- I see.
- We can work it out.

242
00:07:52,293 --> 00:07:53,462
Then Dae Ho,

243
00:07:53,463 --> 00:07:57,803
have you known Soo Geun personally since you lived in Yangpyeong?

244
00:07:58,003 --> 00:08:00,002
I only heard rumors about Soo Geun...

245
00:08:00,003 --> 00:08:01,003
because he was so famous.

246
00:08:01,004 --> 00:08:02,242
- He's from Yangpyeong.
- They have a big age gap.

247
00:08:02,243 --> 00:08:04,242
He was so great at hosting events...

248
00:08:04,243 --> 00:08:06,472
that there were a lot of rumors about him, but we never met then.

249
00:08:06,473 --> 00:08:07,872
Right. We were many grades apart,

250
00:08:07,873 --> 00:08:08,882
- we couldn't meet each other.
- Exactly.

251
00:08:08,883 --> 00:08:10,782
What's the age gap between you? It might be 3 or 4 years?

252
00:08:10,783 --> 00:08:12,252
- Dae Ho is the same age as me.
- No, it's bigger than that.

253
00:08:12,253 --> 00:08:13,782
- Dae Ho is?
- I'm the same age as Kyung Hoon.

254
00:08:13,783 --> 00:08:14,852
He's younger than Hee Chul?

255
00:08:14,853 --> 00:08:17,022
- Dae Ho was born in 1984?
- I'm younger than him.

256
00:08:17,023 --> 00:08:18,023
Really?

257
00:08:18,024 --> 00:08:19,422
I have a question.

258
00:08:19,423 --> 00:08:21,992
Soo Geun told us many times that he had to go downtown...

259
00:08:21,993 --> 00:08:23,462
- to make a phone call.
- Right.

260
00:08:23,463 --> 00:08:24,892
And people in Yangpyeong tried chocolate much later than those...

261
00:08:24,893 --> 00:08:26,332
- in other areas. Is it true?
- Given by American soldiers.

262
00:08:26,333 --> 00:08:29,762
- I've seen American soldiers there.
- He was in elementary school?

263
00:08:29,763 --> 00:08:32,572
I saw American soldiers standing in front of my school.

264
00:08:32,573 --> 00:08:33,932
I was fascinated by them, so I ran to them...

265
00:08:33,933 --> 00:08:35,402
and said hello in English.

266
00:08:35,403 --> 00:08:37,242
Then the American soldiers said hi back to me.

267
00:08:37,243 --> 00:08:38,942
Sometimes they gave me chocolate.

268
00:08:38,943 --> 00:08:41,242
I've seen it in the movie "Taegukgi: Brotherhood of War."

269
00:08:41,243 --> 00:08:45,013
Back in my days, it was rare to see American soldiers in their uniforms.

270
00:08:45,853 --> 00:08:47,682
And the chocolate was so sweet.

271
00:08:47,683 --> 00:08:49,052
When we asked for chocolate,

272
00:08:49,053 --> 00:08:50,452
- They'd toss some from a car.
- they tossed some chocolate...

273
00:08:50,453 --> 00:08:51,882
- from an APC.
- Right.

274
00:08:51,883 --> 00:08:53,222
- Oh, really?
- Right, from an APC.

275
00:08:53,223 --> 00:08:56,022
You must've been surprised when you first tried chocolate.

276
00:08:56,023 --> 00:08:58,222
- It was amazing.
- It was your first time trying it.

277
00:08:58,223 --> 00:09:00,433
That's when I decided to run away from home for the first time.

278
00:09:01,293 --> 00:09:03,503
- Because it was delicious?
- I was like, "How delicious!"

279
00:09:03,903 --> 00:09:06,133
I realized there was a bigger world to see.

280
00:09:06,933 --> 00:09:07,933
He was amazed by its taste.

281
00:09:08,803 --> 00:09:09,872
- He consumed sugar...
- So...

282
00:09:09,873 --> 00:09:12,513
He consumed sugar directly from salvia flowers.

283
00:09:12,743 --> 00:09:14,742
The transfer form to Men on a Mission.

284
00:09:14,743 --> 00:09:17,082
The names, Kim Dae Ho and Kwak Joon Bin.

285
00:09:17,083 --> 00:09:18,243
Welcome!

286
00:09:18,853 --> 00:09:19,853
It's nice to meet you.

287
00:09:20,353 --> 00:09:23,382
First, we'll check out their nicknames.

288
00:09:23,383 --> 00:09:24,652
Dae Ho's nickname...

289
00:09:24,653 --> 00:09:26,523
Actually, I've had no nicknames.

290
00:09:26,893 --> 00:09:30,162
I've only had some nicknames derived from my first name.

291
00:09:30,163 --> 00:09:31,223
For example?

292
00:09:31,323 --> 00:09:33,033
Since my name was Dae Ho, I was called Daechoo.

293
00:09:33,463 --> 00:09:34,993
- Right. That makes sense.
- Or Daechoon.

294
00:09:35,133 --> 00:09:36,832
- Right.
- I had nicknames like that.

295
00:09:36,833 --> 00:09:38,432
My friends used to call me Hoechori.

296
00:09:38,433 --> 00:09:40,032
Maybe Dae Ho likes to exercise.

297
00:09:40,033 --> 00:09:42,872
Many people say he's like Kian84.

298
00:09:42,873 --> 00:09:43,943
Oh, that.

299
00:09:44,043 --> 00:09:47,072
- I come across as free-spirited...
- That's right.

300
00:09:47,073 --> 00:09:48,612
and unconventional.

301
00:09:48,613 --> 00:09:52,043
- Such image is similar to Kian84's.
- I can see that.

302
00:09:52,153 --> 00:09:55,622
But when we ate together... We had a barbecue the other day.

303
00:09:55,623 --> 00:09:58,052
And he told me not to wash onion and lettuce.

304
00:09:58,053 --> 00:09:59,753
- Why?
- To eat them in their wild form.

305
00:10:00,453 --> 00:10:02,122
- He doesn't wash vegetables.
- So...

306
00:10:02,123 --> 00:10:03,222
Just the way they came from the nature?

307
00:10:03,223 --> 00:10:04,692
(- Shall we grill some garlic too?
- Of course.)

308
00:10:04,693 --> 00:10:05,763
(Grabbing)

309
00:10:06,563 --> 00:10:08,432
(We should wash them first.)

310
00:10:08,433 --> 00:10:09,433
(What?)

311
00:10:10,333 --> 00:10:12,473
(They have different perspectives on hygiene.)

312
00:10:12,573 --> 00:10:14,573
(The inner layers of onion are clean.)

313
00:10:14,673 --> 00:10:16,573
(It's entirely Dae Ho's own personal opinion.)

314
00:10:16,673 --> 00:10:19,113
(There's something I've always wanted to try.)

315
00:10:19,513 --> 00:10:21,473
(I want to try vegetable leaves eaten by a bug.)

316
00:10:21,573 --> 00:10:23,643
(If you look closely, you can find a bug.)

317
00:10:24,683 --> 00:10:25,683
(Putting it into his mouth)

318
00:10:25,913 --> 00:10:27,283
(The unconventional bug eating show)

319
00:10:27,483 --> 00:10:29,583
- Why don't you wash it with water?
- Packaged vegetables are clean.

320
00:10:29,723 --> 00:10:31,422
- But that's not the reason.
- But still...

321
00:10:31,423 --> 00:10:33,122
- You revealed your house.
- Yes.

322
00:10:33,123 --> 00:10:35,052
And you went into an inflatable pool, right?

323
00:10:35,053 --> 00:10:36,622
- I live in a house with a yard.
- I see.

324
00:10:36,623 --> 00:10:39,692
So I set up a small above-ground pool in the yard.

325
00:10:39,693 --> 00:10:41,632
Soo Geun must know this. Back in the day,

326
00:10:41,633 --> 00:10:44,202
- in valley water, - People used to wash fruits.

327
00:10:44,203 --> 00:10:47,372
- we put some fruits in the water.
- Many people did that.

328
00:10:47,373 --> 00:10:49,403
I tried that in my yard.

329
00:10:49,703 --> 00:10:52,212
But people said it was ridiculous to wash fruits with the water...

330
00:10:52,213 --> 00:10:54,043
- in which I swam.
- Right, of course.

331
00:10:54,143 --> 00:10:56,813
I just wanted to reminisce old memories from my childhood.

332
00:10:57,243 --> 00:10:59,212
- That was my intention.
- But valley water is flowing water.

333
00:10:59,213 --> 00:11:02,113
- You went into the pool.
- Right. People pointed that out.

334
00:11:02,283 --> 00:11:03,723
I had nothing to say to refute that.

335
00:11:03,953 --> 00:11:05,382
Because they were right about that.

336
00:11:05,383 --> 00:11:08,192
But I didn't think it was dirty.

337
00:11:08,193 --> 00:11:10,723
- Right.
- I did it for fun.

338
00:11:10,863 --> 00:11:13,363
But it made some people uncomfortable.

339
00:11:13,633 --> 00:11:16,563
- He didn't care.
- That's how I got the nickname...

340
00:11:16,703 --> 00:11:17,903
Kian84 of announcers.

341
00:11:18,063 --> 00:11:20,272
- That's probably the reason.
- Clearly, Dae Ho is...

342
00:11:20,273 --> 00:11:22,342
different from me and Jang Hoon.

343
00:11:22,343 --> 00:11:23,602
- He is totally different from us.
- Yes. You two are clean and tidy.

344
00:11:23,603 --> 00:11:27,673
For example, I wouldn't mind sharing a bathtub with Jang Hoon.

345
00:11:27,943 --> 00:11:29,582
But I wouldn't be able to share it with you.

346
00:11:29,583 --> 00:11:32,012
Why must we share a bathtub? And there's another thing.

347
00:11:32,013 --> 00:11:33,482
- You wouldn't mind...
- There would be...

348
00:11:33,483 --> 00:11:36,153
- You'd share it with me, right?
- There'd be a lot of water in it.

349
00:11:36,523 --> 00:11:39,092
- Well, people are different.
- By any chance, did you do it...

350
00:11:39,093 --> 00:11:41,393
- on purpose to make the show fun?
- That must be the case.

351
00:11:41,593 --> 00:11:45,293
No. I'm telling you the truth. I was just being myself.

352
00:11:45,663 --> 00:11:47,763
Some people found it fun...

353
00:11:48,133 --> 00:11:50,302
while the others thought it was disgusting...

354
00:11:50,303 --> 00:11:51,532
- and uncomfortable to watch.
- They wouldn't ask him to do it.

355
00:11:51,533 --> 00:11:52,933
- That's right.
- Anyway, Dae Ho,

356
00:11:53,003 --> 00:11:54,632
- you gave up on marriage, right?
- Sorry?

357
00:11:54,633 --> 00:11:55,973
- You gave up on getting married?
- Are you married?

358
00:11:56,103 --> 00:11:57,743
Marriage? I'm not a misogamist.

359
00:11:58,373 --> 00:12:00,012
But showing that kind of side of you...

360
00:12:00,013 --> 00:12:02,383
wouldn't help you get married soon.

361
00:12:03,243 --> 00:12:05,113
- He's confident.
- I'll figure out my life.

362
00:12:06,683 --> 00:12:08,613
- Because he's married now...
- That's not good.

363
00:12:09,453 --> 00:12:11,452
- He's the only one among us...
- He's like a marriage expert.

364
00:12:11,453 --> 00:12:13,493
who's been married twice.

365
00:12:14,153 --> 00:12:17,022
How dare you act like you know it all when you have no experience?

366
00:12:17,023 --> 00:12:19,062
- How dare you?
- He's like a marriage specialist.

367
00:12:19,063 --> 00:12:21,232
- Our marriage specialist...
- He sounds like an expert.

368
00:12:21,233 --> 00:12:22,963
Have you been married twice?

369
00:12:23,233 --> 00:12:24,732
- Say nothing if you haven't.
- I'm sorry.

370
00:12:24,733 --> 00:12:26,532
- Thank you for the advice.
- He's a marriage professional.

371
00:12:26,533 --> 00:12:28,773
- Exactly.
- He's an expert.

372
00:12:28,903 --> 00:12:31,142
I don't want to stay single forever, so...

373
00:12:31,143 --> 00:12:32,243
- When do you want to get married?
- Wasn't that good?

374
00:12:33,313 --> 00:12:36,243
Not long ago, I met a fortune teller in one of my YouTube videos.

375
00:12:36,443 --> 00:12:39,553
I was told that I was destined to meet someone before I turned 50.

376
00:12:39,983 --> 00:12:41,913
But if I don't get married before I turn 50,

377
00:12:42,283 --> 00:12:44,483
I might get married at a very late age, apparently.

378
00:12:44,583 --> 00:12:46,892
So I may get married before 50 if I get lucky...

379
00:12:46,893 --> 00:12:48,792
and meet someone to love.

380
00:12:48,793 --> 00:12:50,692
If you don't get married before 50...

381
00:12:50,693 --> 00:12:52,793
At what age will you get married if you get married late?

382
00:12:53,263 --> 00:12:54,893
At the age of 60.

383
00:12:55,333 --> 00:12:58,302
- If it doesn't work before he's 50.
- In my mid 50s, maybe.

384
00:12:58,303 --> 00:13:01,072
Aside from Dae Ho's lack of hygienic habits,

385
00:13:01,073 --> 00:13:04,802
- Dae Ho is from a very big family.
- Right. That's even worse...

386
00:13:04,803 --> 00:13:07,273
- When his family gathers...
- Why?

387
00:13:07,373 --> 00:13:09,542
- Young people these days...
- From his wife's perspective.

388
00:13:09,543 --> 00:13:11,742
We don't do that now,

389
00:13:11,743 --> 00:13:13,983
but we have made kimchi with 1,400 heads of napa cabbage.

390
00:13:14,353 --> 00:13:15,582
- Did you say 1,400?
- You mean 1,400 heads of cabbage?

391
00:13:15,583 --> 00:13:17,182
- Even with 140 heads of it...
- How many...

392
00:13:17,183 --> 00:13:18,382
How many of your family members gathered to do it?

393
00:13:18,383 --> 00:13:20,552
- The whole neighborhood gathered.
- Acquaintances...

394
00:13:20,553 --> 00:13:22,823
- All of them made kimchi together.
- They help each other make kimchi.

395
00:13:22,923 --> 00:13:24,222
Even making kimchi with 100 heads of napa cabbage wouldn't be easy.

396
00:13:24,223 --> 00:13:25,932
- Of course.
- If his future wife hears...

397
00:13:25,933 --> 00:13:28,263
about his family making that much kimchi, she could be terrified.

398
00:13:28,633 --> 00:13:30,432
But people have different preferences.

399
00:13:30,433 --> 00:13:32,602
- Some people like a big family.
- That's true.

400
00:13:32,603 --> 00:13:35,633
- After that footage was revealed, - I know some of such people.

401
00:13:35,843 --> 00:13:38,973
many people worried if I might not get married.

402
00:13:39,173 --> 00:13:41,543
But surprisingly, there's a niche market.

403
00:13:42,243 --> 00:13:43,812
- A niche market?
- I mean, some women want...

404
00:13:43,813 --> 00:13:46,313
- a man from a big family. Exactly.
- Those who lived a lonely life.

405
00:13:46,583 --> 00:13:49,423
If your fiance says, "I like you,"

406
00:13:49,683 --> 00:13:51,722
- "but seeing your family often..."
- "That won't be easy for me."

407
00:13:51,723 --> 00:13:52,992
- "will be hard," what would you do?
- He wouldn't marry her.

408
00:13:52,993 --> 00:13:55,763
If I love her, I could make adjustments.

409
00:13:56,493 --> 00:13:57,562
- Right.
- Then there'd be no problem.

410
00:13:57,563 --> 00:13:59,232
But if his family is that large,

411
00:13:59,233 --> 00:14:00,762
the absence of a few of them wouldn't be noticeable.

412
00:14:00,763 --> 00:14:03,563
- That's right. That's a good point.
- Right.

413
00:14:03,663 --> 00:14:04,802
I didn't think of that.

414
00:14:04,803 --> 00:14:07,372
- They wouldn't care so much.
- I agree.

415
00:14:07,373 --> 00:14:09,002
She'd always have a chance...

416
00:14:09,003 --> 00:14:10,643
- to bond with my family.
- That's right.

417
00:14:10,803 --> 00:14:13,543
Joon Bin's nickname is... What is this?

418
00:14:13,773 --> 00:14:15,672
He wrote, "Honorary Chinese."

419
00:14:15,673 --> 00:14:17,313
My nickname...

420
00:14:17,943 --> 00:14:20,512
So many foreigners I met thought I was Chinese.

421
00:14:20,513 --> 00:14:21,952
- Oh, that's why?
- I saw many people asking...

422
00:14:21,953 --> 00:14:23,382
if you were Chinese in your YouTube videos.

423
00:14:23,383 --> 00:14:25,723
- That's right.
- They just say hi to me in Chinese.

424
00:14:26,153 --> 00:14:27,293
(You're Chinese, yes?)

425
00:14:27,893 --> 00:14:29,263
(- Are you from China?
- No.)

426
00:14:29,463 --> 00:14:30,622
(Are you Chinese?)

427
00:14:30,623 --> 00:14:31,723
(I am Korean.)

428
00:14:32,193 --> 00:14:33,463
(- Hi.
- Ni hao.)

429
00:14:33,563 --> 00:14:34,563
(No "ni hao.")

430
00:14:34,633 --> 00:14:36,403
(But it's true. I'm not Chinese.)

431
00:14:36,733 --> 00:14:38,533
(Extremely shocked)

432
00:14:39,233 --> 00:14:41,803
I heard that a lot even before I started my YouTube channel.

433
00:14:42,073 --> 00:14:44,503
Even when I was in my early 20s, when I traveled overseas,

434
00:14:44,643 --> 00:14:47,942
so many people spoke to me in Chinese, and I didn't like that.

435
00:14:47,943 --> 00:14:49,782
But now, I just say thank you in Chinese and go my way.

436
00:14:49,783 --> 00:14:50,812
"Thank you" in Chinese?

437
00:14:50,813 --> 00:14:53,082
- That happens a lot to many people.
- Do you actually speak Chinese?

438
00:14:53,083 --> 00:14:54,313
I don't speak Chinese at all.

439
00:14:54,483 --> 00:14:55,512
I just say, "Thank you."

440
00:14:55,513 --> 00:14:57,483
"I like it." And then I just go.

441
00:14:57,653 --> 00:14:59,192
- It means he likes it.
- We have an honorary Chinese here.

442
00:14:59,193 --> 00:15:00,823
What was your nickname when you were a child?

443
00:15:00,953 --> 00:15:02,493
When I was a child, I was called a pig.

444
00:15:02,963 --> 00:15:04,162
(Feeling familiarity)

445
00:15:04,163 --> 00:15:05,692
- That's how kids are.
- Did you have any other nicknames?

446
00:15:05,693 --> 00:15:07,062
- He and Ho Dong...
- Kids always do that.

447
00:15:07,063 --> 00:15:08,363
- have a lot in common.
- I was always called...

448
00:15:08,463 --> 00:15:09,732
- a pig or fatty.
- I see.

449
00:15:09,733 --> 00:15:12,402
- "Fatty?"
- A nice version was "piglet."

450
00:15:12,403 --> 00:15:13,633
- "Piglet?"
- I was called that too.

451
00:15:13,733 --> 00:15:16,443
- I have the face of a piglet.
- Were you always plump?

452
00:15:16,973 --> 00:15:19,413
I've been maintaining being overweight since I was little.

453
00:15:19,943 --> 00:15:21,012
(His body shape hasn't changed.)

454
00:15:21,013 --> 00:15:23,413
- You've been maintaining?
- What effort did you make to do so?

455
00:15:23,783 --> 00:15:25,813
- I've been sticking to my diet...
- Diet?

456
00:15:26,553 --> 00:15:27,712
and minimizing the time I spent exercising.

457
00:15:27,713 --> 00:15:30,853
Did you eat two servings of ramyeon before going to bed?

458
00:15:30,983 --> 00:15:33,653
I ate 2 servings of ones with soup or 3 servings of ones without soup.

459
00:15:34,523 --> 00:15:35,592
You ate five servings of ramyeon?

460
00:15:35,593 --> 00:15:36,962
- No, separately.
- Separately.

461
00:15:36,963 --> 00:15:38,162
- I ate it as a late-night snack.
- Separately?

462
00:15:38,163 --> 00:15:39,632
I ate three servings of ones that have no soup.

463
00:15:39,633 --> 00:15:40,962
- The serving size is smaller.
- When I ate ones with soup,

464
00:15:40,963 --> 00:15:42,062
I had two servings with rice.

465
00:15:42,063 --> 00:15:43,402
- Before you went to bed?
- Yes.

466
00:15:43,403 --> 00:15:45,263
It feels good to go to sleep after eating so much, right?

467
00:15:45,403 --> 00:15:47,233
But I didn't exercise, unlike you.

468
00:15:47,573 --> 00:15:50,473
I avoided exercising as much as possible.

469
00:15:50,673 --> 00:15:52,102
- I played video games instead.
- He was strict with himself.

470
00:15:52,103 --> 00:15:53,573
- It's not something to brag about.
- He did a good job.

471
00:15:53,943 --> 00:15:55,312
(He'd be the best if it were something to brag about.)

472
00:15:55,313 --> 00:15:56,942
- He did a great job.
- By the way... What was it?

473
00:15:56,943 --> 00:15:59,513
I heard that the news about Kwaktube getting marriage...

474
00:15:59,683 --> 00:16:01,452
- made many people angry.
- Why?

475
00:16:01,453 --> 00:16:02,952
- Why did they get angry?
- Were they his female fans?

476
00:16:02,953 --> 00:16:05,122
- I thought my fans would be mad, - Why were they angry?

477
00:16:05,123 --> 00:16:06,423
but they congratulated me sincerely.

478
00:16:06,793 --> 00:16:08,322
They were surprised, but they were happy for me.

479
00:16:08,323 --> 00:16:09,523
Who got mad? Did you get mad, Yeong Cheol?

480
00:16:09,823 --> 00:16:11,192
The first person I told the news was Jun Hyun Moo.

481
00:16:11,193 --> 00:16:12,493
I said, "Hyun Moo, I'm getting married."

482
00:16:13,133 --> 00:16:15,163
He sighed deeply and said, "Everyone is getting married."

483
00:16:15,263 --> 00:16:16,562
"But how come even you are getting married too?"

484
00:16:16,563 --> 00:16:19,402
- He was really sad about the news.
- He was sad?

485
00:16:19,403 --> 00:16:21,572
And when Dae Ho heard the news... It was first time hearing about it.

486
00:16:21,573 --> 00:16:23,103
All the others congratulated me.

487
00:16:23,273 --> 00:16:25,473
I liked how he reacted. He said, "I won't congratulate you."

488
00:16:26,413 --> 00:16:28,042
- We first met then.
- You see...

489
00:16:28,043 --> 00:16:31,613
- Dae Ho, you're not very sociable.
- Right. I can see that.

490
00:16:31,713 --> 00:16:33,652
He said he wouldn't congratulate me. I was confused.

491
00:16:33,653 --> 00:16:35,312
It's not that I didn't congratulate him.

492
00:16:35,313 --> 00:16:36,722
I wouldn't insist on congratulating anyone on marriage.

493
00:16:36,723 --> 00:16:37,852
- What's that?
- What does that mean?

494
00:16:37,853 --> 00:16:40,152
I believe that sharing sorrow with others...

495
00:16:40,153 --> 00:16:42,153
help one deal with the emotion.

496
00:16:42,353 --> 00:16:43,892
- But so many people already...
- So you think...

497
00:16:43,893 --> 00:16:45,422
congratulated him... I mean at a good event...

498
00:16:45,423 --> 00:16:47,632
- Do you have an over-inflated ego?
- What I'm saying is...

499
00:16:47,633 --> 00:16:48,932
- "While others congratulate him,"
- Dae Ho.

500
00:16:48,933 --> 00:16:50,062
"I won't congratulate him."

501
00:16:50,063 --> 00:16:53,733
I mean, it's up to you whether you congratulate or not,

502
00:16:54,033 --> 00:16:55,602
- but you don't have to say that.
- That's right.

503
00:16:55,603 --> 00:16:57,302
- "I won't congratulate you."
- To be exact,

504
00:16:57,303 --> 00:16:58,973
I didn't say, "I won't congratulate you."

505
00:16:59,143 --> 00:17:02,313
I said I thought it was unnecessary for me to congratulate him.

506
00:17:02,683 --> 00:17:03,913
But listen to me. For example...

507
00:17:04,113 --> 00:17:05,912
- What's the difference?
- So he doesn't want to do it.

508
00:17:05,913 --> 00:17:06,952
He sounds like an attention seeker.

509
00:17:06,953 --> 00:17:08,412
- People like him always say...
- Dae Ho.

510
00:17:08,413 --> 00:17:10,723
- Sorry, but do you have friends?
- No.

511
00:17:11,583 --> 00:17:13,052
- You guys are my first friends.
- He's so peculiar.

512
00:17:13,053 --> 00:17:14,752
- Exactly.
- Did something happen...

513
00:17:14,753 --> 00:17:16,493
that made you this twisted?

514
00:17:16,663 --> 00:17:17,892
(Twisted)

515
00:17:17,893 --> 00:17:19,192
If there's no reason,

516
00:17:19,193 --> 00:17:21,663
why would he be overly twisted?

517
00:17:21,733 --> 00:17:23,762
- I mean...
- You could've thought to yourself.

518
00:17:23,763 --> 00:17:25,503
- It's just the way I expressed it.
- Exactly.

519
00:17:25,803 --> 00:17:27,332
I'm happy for him. I really am,

520
00:17:27,333 --> 00:17:30,403
but I wouldn't say something like, "Joon Bin, I'm so jealous."

521
00:17:30,873 --> 00:17:33,812
I would just think to myself he must be happy.

522
00:17:33,813 --> 00:17:35,542
What he said was rather memorable.

523
00:17:35,543 --> 00:17:36,982
So many people congratulated me,

524
00:17:36,983 --> 00:17:39,142
- That's why you still remember it.
- but Dae Ho was different.

525
00:17:39,143 --> 00:17:40,912
- I was impressed...
- I'll say such a thing from now on.

526
00:17:40,913 --> 00:17:42,883
realizing that he was just the way he seemed on TV.

527
00:17:43,983 --> 00:17:46,593
- I found him so cool.
- Kyung Hoon quietly said...

528
00:17:46,923 --> 00:17:48,252
he sounded like an attention seeker.

529
00:17:48,253 --> 00:17:50,762
- What? Oh, that's right.
- I didn't mean it like that.

530
00:17:50,763 --> 00:17:51,922
- Right.
- He's like an attention seeker.

531
00:17:51,923 --> 00:17:54,133
- He seems like an attention seeker.
- Indeed.

532
00:17:54,593 --> 00:17:56,963
They say you should be happy if you seek attention as a kid.

533
00:17:56,988 --> 00:17:59,758
Yeong Cheol, are you happy for him? Or are you sad?

534
00:18:00,203 --> 00:18:01,473
- You mean, Kwaktube?
- Yes.

535
00:18:01,498 --> 00:18:03,068
Actually, a thought just crossed my mind.

536
00:18:03,603 --> 00:18:05,173
"Even Kwaktube got married..."

537
00:18:06,513 --> 00:18:07,773
"Even Kwaktube got married..."

538
00:18:09,443 --> 00:18:11,913
- "Even Kwaktube got married?"
- You think you're better than him?

539
00:18:12,813 --> 00:18:15,213
- He thinks he's a superstar.
- I'm so curious.

540
00:18:15,383 --> 00:18:17,053
- He thinks he's a real celebrity.
- What I'm saying is...

541
00:18:17,123 --> 00:18:18,622
What makes you better than him?

542
00:18:18,623 --> 00:18:19,992
- Kwaktube is...
- I'm more curious about it.

543
00:18:19,993 --> 00:18:22,452
Kwaktube is much younger than you to begin with.

544
00:18:22,453 --> 00:18:24,162
- I mean, even he got married.
- In every aspect...

545
00:18:24,163 --> 00:18:26,363
- So I think I can get married too.
- What makes you better than him?

546
00:18:26,963 --> 00:18:29,092
Let's forget who's handsome or not.

547
00:18:29,093 --> 00:18:30,532
Kwaktube is cute.

548
00:18:30,533 --> 00:18:32,332
- Oh, that's true.
- Yeong Cheol is cute too, you know.

549
00:18:32,333 --> 00:18:33,572
- What are you talking about?
- Come on.

550
00:18:33,573 --> 00:18:34,972
- I don't think he's cute.
- Hey.

551
00:18:34,973 --> 00:18:36,043
Kwaktube...

552
00:18:36,673 --> 00:18:38,442
- Kwaktube is a little...
- I don't agree that he's cute.

553
00:18:38,443 --> 00:18:41,142
- Really?
- Kwaktube, saying such a thing...

554
00:18:41,143 --> 00:18:42,612
is not helpful for Yeong Cheol.

555
00:18:42,613 --> 00:18:44,542
Dae Ho, be completely honest with us.

556
00:18:44,543 --> 00:18:46,113
- Is Yeong Cheol cute or not?
- It's not helpful for him.

557
00:18:46,813 --> 00:18:48,013
I admit that he's famous.

558
00:18:48,483 --> 00:18:49,552
But is he cute or not?

559
00:18:49,553 --> 00:18:52,552
I don't really think he is.

560
00:18:52,553 --> 00:18:53,693
(Cathartic)

561
00:18:53,923 --> 00:18:55,793
- He's not cute.
- That's right.

562
00:18:55,953 --> 00:18:57,092
But he could be happy with himself.

563
00:18:57,093 --> 00:19:01,133
Where did you say you met your wife?

564
00:19:01,233 --> 00:19:03,732
We met on a blind date and started dating a long time ago.

565
00:19:03,733 --> 00:19:05,462
But we broke up once.

566
00:19:05,463 --> 00:19:07,403
We got back together after I started my YouTube channel.

567
00:19:07,833 --> 00:19:09,302
- After you started your channel?
- Why did you two break up?

568
00:19:09,303 --> 00:19:10,842
I didn't call her often as I became busy.

569
00:19:10,843 --> 00:19:12,472
We became distant and broke up.

570
00:19:12,473 --> 00:19:14,672
- But we were meant to be together.
- Right. It's fate.

571
00:19:14,673 --> 00:19:16,583
- Who contacted again first?
- I did.

572
00:19:17,743 --> 00:19:20,352
- I contacted her first...
- Who dumped who when you broke up?

573
00:19:20,353 --> 00:19:23,122
I wouldn't say "dumped" per se, but I asked for the breakup.

574
00:19:23,123 --> 00:19:24,322
- Really?
- Oh, my.

575
00:19:24,323 --> 00:19:26,353
- What a baddie.
- But when we got back together...

576
00:19:26,593 --> 00:19:28,222
- To think you'd ask for it.
- I couldn't pay attention to her,

577
00:19:28,223 --> 00:19:29,252
so we broke up.

578
00:19:29,253 --> 00:19:31,762
Your wife is indeed kind.

579
00:19:31,763 --> 00:19:33,532
- I know, right?
- She's too kind.

580
00:19:33,533 --> 00:19:34,892
- She got back together...
- She's really kind.

581
00:19:34,893 --> 00:19:36,162
- Right?
- Who dumped her.

582
00:19:36,163 --> 00:19:38,303
- with the man...
- Exactly.

583
00:19:38,433 --> 00:19:40,472
who got in touch after dumping her.

584
00:19:40,473 --> 00:19:41,673
That's real love.

585
00:19:41,773 --> 00:19:44,572
What did you like most about her?

586
00:19:44,573 --> 00:19:46,242
I have low self-esteem,

587
00:19:46,243 --> 00:19:47,972
but my wife is the complete opposite.

588
00:19:47,973 --> 00:19:50,112
- Is that so?
- I see the world...

589
00:19:50,113 --> 00:19:51,282
very pessimistically,

590
00:19:51,283 --> 00:19:52,583
- almost as much as Jang Hoon.
- That's...

591
00:19:52,683 --> 00:19:53,852
- Hey.
- Excuse me,

592
00:19:53,853 --> 00:19:54,983
but we've only met today.

593
00:19:55,783 --> 00:19:57,182
Saying that on the first encounter.

594
00:19:57,183 --> 00:20:00,523
How would you know how pessimistic I am?

595
00:20:00,723 --> 00:20:02,323
- He's an honest guy.
- Just how?

596
00:20:02,423 --> 00:20:03,993
What you said just now is also pessimistic.

597
00:20:04,823 --> 00:20:06,232
Be nice to him, will you?

598
00:20:06,233 --> 00:20:07,432
- Hey.
- That just now...

599
00:20:07,433 --> 00:20:08,662
was very pessimistic.

600
00:20:08,663 --> 00:20:11,862
Earlier, I said something bright about his wife,

601
00:20:11,863 --> 00:20:13,602
like how nice a person she was.

602
00:20:13,603 --> 00:20:14,702
That was optimistic.

603
00:20:14,703 --> 00:20:16,443
I was being optimistic.

604
00:20:16,603 --> 00:20:18,602
Does everyone in the YouTube industry know that...

605
00:20:18,603 --> 00:20:19,873
Jang Hoon is pessimistic?

606
00:20:20,213 --> 00:20:22,042
He has the kind of personality I like,

607
00:20:22,043 --> 00:20:23,112
- I see.
- but others may find it...

608
00:20:23,113 --> 00:20:24,243
uncomfortable.

609
00:20:24,313 --> 00:20:25,382
Absolutely.

610
00:20:25,383 --> 00:20:28,412
When you joined the same company as Seo Jang Hoon,

611
00:20:28,413 --> 00:20:30,882
Ho Dong was like, "Who is he?"

612
00:20:30,883 --> 00:20:33,452
But Jang Hoon was thoughtful and said,

613
00:20:33,453 --> 00:20:35,492
"Since Kwaktube is in the same company,"

614
00:20:35,493 --> 00:20:36,722
"he should come on our show."

615
00:20:36,723 --> 00:20:38,422
- That's right.
- I still remember that.

616
00:20:38,423 --> 00:20:40,232
- That...
- Did I really say that?

617
00:20:40,233 --> 00:20:42,132
- You did.
- What did I say?

618
00:20:42,133 --> 00:20:44,203
You asked, "What is that?"

619
00:20:45,033 --> 00:20:46,702
One was being thoughtful while the other had no idea.

620
00:20:46,703 --> 00:20:50,242
He kept saying things like, "Must we take care of every small fry?"

621
00:20:50,243 --> 00:20:52,203
(Kwaktube, "That" or "Small fry")

622
00:20:52,373 --> 00:20:54,012
"Must we take care of small fries too?"

623
00:20:54,013 --> 00:20:55,373
"Even the nobodies?"

624
00:20:55,743 --> 00:20:57,242
- Nobodies?
- "What a waste of time."

625
00:20:57,243 --> 00:20:58,713
I did hear him say "nobody."

626
00:20:58,813 --> 00:21:00,313
But you know nothing about him.

627
00:21:00,783 --> 00:21:03,752
Kwaktube uploaded vlogs of his honeymoon.

628
00:21:03,753 --> 00:21:05,023
Where was his honeymoon?

629
00:21:05,153 --> 00:21:06,793
What? Abroad.

630
00:21:06,923 --> 00:21:08,052
He traveled abroad.

631
00:21:08,053 --> 00:21:10,693
- I went to Jeju Island.
- Was it Jeju Island?

632
00:21:10,893 --> 00:21:12,162
- You so didn't watch it.
- What?

633
00:21:12,163 --> 00:21:13,832
- Was it Jeju Island?
- Is Jeju Island abroad?

634
00:21:13,833 --> 00:21:15,092
- It's in Korea.
- Hold on.

635
00:21:15,093 --> 00:21:17,062
- It's abroad to him.
- The background looked overseas.

636
00:21:17,063 --> 00:21:18,362
He even made...

637
00:21:18,363 --> 00:21:19,672
- a peace sign for the vlog.
- A couple's Jeju Island...

638
00:21:19,673 --> 00:21:21,772
- He went to Europe.
- Yes, I went to Europe.

639
00:21:21,773 --> 00:21:23,743
- Is that so?
- I watched the videos.

640
00:21:23,973 --> 00:21:27,043
Doesn't your wife find it uncomfortable?

641
00:21:27,073 --> 00:21:29,142
I didn't want to take videos of our honeymoon...

642
00:21:29,143 --> 00:21:30,612
- because I'm always taking videos.
- Right.

643
00:21:30,613 --> 00:21:33,053
- It's your job.
- But my wife told me...

644
00:21:33,253 --> 00:21:36,853
to take them as memories and upload them if I want to.

645
00:21:37,023 --> 00:21:38,052
She suggested taking videos.

646
00:21:38,053 --> 00:21:39,552
I'm very happy. Honeymoon.

647
00:21:39,553 --> 00:21:40,892
- Honeymoon?
- Yes.

648
00:21:40,893 --> 00:21:42,123
Ta-da.

649
00:21:43,423 --> 00:21:44,493
What's this?

650
00:21:44,963 --> 00:21:46,022
A surprise event.

651
00:21:46,023 --> 00:21:47,033
For real?

652
00:21:47,133 --> 00:21:48,133
Gosh.

653
00:21:48,134 --> 00:21:50,432
We've become "Mr." and "Mrs."

654
00:21:50,433 --> 00:21:52,033
Traveling is hardest for pregnant women.

655
00:21:52,363 --> 00:21:55,233
But this is a one and only opportunity.

656
00:21:55,533 --> 00:21:56,742
I promise this won't be the last.

657
00:21:56,743 --> 00:21:59,503
(Revealed his priceless memories that won't come around again)

658
00:21:59,613 --> 00:22:01,043
All right. "Former occupation."

659
00:22:01,913 --> 00:22:04,042
We know their former occupations. Dae Ho was...

660
00:22:04,043 --> 00:22:05,242
- an announcer.
- MBC announcer.

661
00:22:05,243 --> 00:22:06,852
- A former announcer.
- Yes.

662
00:22:06,853 --> 00:22:08,453
Did you always want to become one?

663
00:22:08,513 --> 00:22:09,682
Or did you just end up becoming one?

664
00:22:09,683 --> 00:22:11,782
No, my dream wasn't to become an announcer at first.

665
00:22:11,783 --> 00:22:14,752
Actually, it's a surprise even to this day that I'm on TV.

666
00:22:14,753 --> 00:22:17,293
- First, I'm an extreme introvert.
- Is that so?

667
00:22:17,463 --> 00:22:18,822
- I tend to shy away...
- Really?

668
00:22:18,823 --> 00:22:20,132
from setting out,

669
00:22:20,133 --> 00:22:22,333
speaking up, and such.

670
00:22:22,433 --> 00:22:25,833
I used to hang out with small groups of people.

671
00:22:26,103 --> 00:22:28,002
But after entering college,

672
00:22:28,003 --> 00:22:29,233
I barely studied.

673
00:22:29,703 --> 00:22:31,572
I didn't get sufficient grades,

674
00:22:31,573 --> 00:22:33,012
so I wondered what I could do...

675
00:22:33,013 --> 00:22:35,343
and which company to join.

676
00:22:35,673 --> 00:22:38,012
I have a voice my parents passed on to me.

677
00:22:38,013 --> 00:22:39,442
- And...
- You've got a great voice.

678
00:22:39,443 --> 00:22:42,982
I don't look bad to the point where it's hard...

679
00:22:42,983 --> 00:22:44,683
on people's eyes.

680
00:22:44,783 --> 00:22:46,082
It's likable.

681
00:22:46,083 --> 00:22:47,852
In short, it's the opposite of Yeong Cheol's.

682
00:22:47,853 --> 00:22:49,792
Probably.

683
00:22:49,793 --> 00:22:51,362
You've got on my bad side.

684
00:22:51,363 --> 00:22:52,492
(Laughing)

685
00:22:52,493 --> 00:22:54,692
That's why I prepared for a year.

686
00:22:54,693 --> 00:22:56,193
- How smart.
- Well...

687
00:22:56,363 --> 00:22:59,502
I was afraid my parents would think I had my head in the clouds...

688
00:22:59,503 --> 00:23:01,032
if I asked them for pocket money.

689
00:23:01,033 --> 00:23:04,703
So I earned it by working as a gosiwon manager.

690
00:23:04,773 --> 00:23:07,272
- You worked hard.
- I was sitting...

691
00:23:07,273 --> 00:23:08,742
in the manager's room after work...

692
00:23:08,743 --> 00:23:11,713
when I saw a small audition notice saying...

693
00:23:11,883 --> 00:23:15,552
"50th Anniversary Special New Employee" on the old TV.

694
00:23:15,553 --> 00:23:17,422
- MBC and Sung Kyu.
- The one Sung Kyu applied to.

695
00:23:17,423 --> 00:23:19,022
- Sung Kyu applied to it.
- Yes.

696
00:23:19,023 --> 00:23:21,322
- He did.
- Anyone who was Korean...

697
00:23:21,323 --> 00:23:23,893
could apply to it regardless of their background.

698
00:23:24,163 --> 00:23:26,793
- To me, it was a golden chance.
- Right.

699
00:23:27,133 --> 00:23:28,533
- I gave it a shot.
- I see.

700
00:23:28,693 --> 00:23:30,662
Out of all the applicants, three people got accepted.

701
00:23:30,663 --> 00:23:33,532
Announcers Kim Cho Rong, Oh Seung Hoon,

702
00:23:33,533 --> 00:23:34,933
and me.

703
00:23:35,103 --> 00:23:36,403
It's not like I won the audition.

704
00:23:36,473 --> 00:23:39,502
Had you not worked as a gosiwon manager...

705
00:23:39,503 --> 00:23:41,273
- and watched the TV, - Yes?

706
00:23:41,473 --> 00:23:42,742
you wouldn't have become an announcer.

707
00:23:42,743 --> 00:23:44,913
- I wouldn't be here right now.
- Gosh.

708
00:23:45,013 --> 00:23:47,753
- Amazing.
- Does that mean you were better...

709
00:23:47,953 --> 00:23:50,722
than Sung Kyu and Announcer Gang Ji Young?

710
00:23:50,723 --> 00:23:52,152
- He made it in the top three.
- He beat them all...

711
00:23:52,153 --> 00:23:53,222
- He did.
- and got in the top three.

712
00:23:53,223 --> 00:23:54,893
The result tells you everything.

713
00:23:55,053 --> 00:23:56,292
- It does.
- Jang Sung Kyu...

714
00:23:56,293 --> 00:23:58,963
The way you say things makes the other person upset.

715
00:23:59,293 --> 00:24:01,493
Here's the kind of personality I picked up about Dae Ho.

716
00:24:01,893 --> 00:24:03,832
Remember how you joked about him being Fake Jang Sung Kyu...

717
00:24:03,833 --> 00:24:05,432
- when he came in?
- Yes.

718
00:24:05,433 --> 00:24:07,003
That had already made him go bananas.

719
00:24:07,303 --> 00:24:09,742
When he came into the classroom?

720
00:24:09,743 --> 00:24:12,572
Kim Dae Ho is well known as Fake Jang Sung Kyu.

721
00:24:12,573 --> 00:24:13,672
(What?)

722
00:24:13,673 --> 00:24:15,342
Judging by your personality,

723
00:24:15,343 --> 00:24:16,512
- What...
- it upset you, right?

724
00:24:16,513 --> 00:24:17,983
- Correct.
- Right?

725
00:24:18,143 --> 00:24:19,712
- Fake Jang Sung Kyu.
- Tell us.

726
00:24:19,713 --> 00:24:21,382
- Think about it.
- Earlier...

727
00:24:21,383 --> 00:24:24,252
Did you feel the urge after seeing Jang Sung Kyu...

728
00:24:24,253 --> 00:24:26,353
leave JTBC and become a successful freelancer?

729
00:24:26,553 --> 00:24:27,922
- What did you think?
- No.

730
00:24:27,923 --> 00:24:29,293
I didn't think he was successful.

731
00:24:29,693 --> 00:24:30,762
- You mean Jang Sung Kyu?
- Oh, my.

732
00:24:30,763 --> 00:24:32,593
- Did you not congratulate him?
- He didn't.

733
00:24:33,663 --> 00:24:35,662
- You didn't, right?
- Listen.

734
00:24:35,663 --> 00:24:38,362
- Dae Ho. When you worked...
- He never congratulates others.

735
00:24:38,363 --> 00:24:40,473
as an announcer in MBC,

736
00:24:40,803 --> 00:24:42,673
what did people say about you?

737
00:24:44,143 --> 00:24:46,272
- Right?
- What did people say about...

738
00:24:46,273 --> 00:24:48,413
your personality and so on?

739
00:24:48,443 --> 00:24:52,713
That's why I'm grateful to my MBC colleagues even to this very day.

740
00:24:52,843 --> 00:24:56,153
- Why?
- They accepted my mean sides.

741
00:24:56,423 --> 00:24:58,652
- What a nice place.
- I started freelancing...

742
00:24:58,653 --> 00:25:00,692
- as soon as I left the company.
- Right.

743
00:25:00,693 --> 00:25:02,392
The majority of my work was in MBC.

744
00:25:02,393 --> 00:25:05,292
Had they seen how I worked,

745
00:25:05,293 --> 00:25:07,563
they could've thought I was sly.

746
00:25:07,633 --> 00:25:09,662
But they saw and accepted me as I was,

747
00:25:09,663 --> 00:25:12,432
which made it possible for me to continue working.

748
00:25:12,433 --> 00:25:14,102
- Here's what I heard.
- Yes?

749
00:25:14,103 --> 00:25:16,802
Getting in the top three of "New Employee" isn't easy.

750
00:25:16,803 --> 00:25:18,002
It's amazing.

751
00:25:18,003 --> 00:25:19,603
- He got through the hurdle.
- Yes.

752
00:25:19,843 --> 00:25:21,073
But apparently, he handed in...

753
00:25:21,673 --> 00:25:24,042
a resignation letter after just three years.

754
00:25:24,043 --> 00:25:25,412
- Really?
- Just three years?

755
00:25:25,413 --> 00:25:27,212
Since that's how I joined the company,

756
00:25:27,213 --> 00:25:29,312
I had no pride as an announcer...

757
00:25:29,313 --> 00:25:32,023
- Gosh.
- or professionalism.

758
00:25:32,123 --> 00:25:33,793
- It's natural.
- There were...

759
00:25:33,893 --> 00:25:35,723
several triggers during shows.

760
00:25:35,923 --> 00:25:38,062
I received a story for a radio show,

761
00:25:38,063 --> 00:25:39,692
but I didn't reply to it with feeling.

762
00:25:39,693 --> 00:25:41,792
"I'm an examinee, but I constantly feel drowsy."

763
00:25:41,793 --> 00:25:43,463
"What should I do?"

764
00:25:44,263 --> 00:25:46,902
"Just sleep" was all I said.

765
00:25:46,903 --> 00:25:48,402
Are you a thinker, Dae Ho?

766
00:25:48,403 --> 00:25:49,732
I'm an extreme thinker.

767
00:25:49,733 --> 00:25:52,172
In radio shows, you have to empathize with the story.

768
00:25:52,173 --> 00:25:55,243
Exactly. "Try drinking a warm cup of milk."

769
00:25:55,413 --> 00:25:58,112
"Try to eat lettuce or wear fluffy socks."

770
00:25:58,113 --> 00:25:59,443
- I should've given advice.
- Right.

771
00:25:59,783 --> 00:26:02,012
The director shut off the console...

772
00:26:02,013 --> 00:26:03,452
- Why?
- and told me...

773
00:26:03,453 --> 00:26:04,753
- to choose between the two options.
- I see.

774
00:26:04,883 --> 00:26:07,093
Retrain yourself as an announcer.

775
00:26:07,393 --> 00:26:09,552
- That's harsh.
- Or quit your job.

776
00:26:09,553 --> 00:26:10,562
- Gosh.
- Really?

777
00:26:10,563 --> 00:26:12,222
- I'm sure some may know, - How harsh.

778
00:26:12,223 --> 00:26:13,633
but after hearing that,

779
00:26:13,693 --> 00:26:16,292
I was in a show called "Consumer Reports."

780
00:26:16,293 --> 00:26:17,803
I was Zero Man.

781
00:26:18,063 --> 00:26:20,602
The Zero Man has to help bring...

782
00:26:20,603 --> 00:26:22,702
the consumers' dissatisfaction rate down to zero.

783
00:26:22,703 --> 00:26:25,303
But I'm completely satisfied with my life.

784
00:26:25,843 --> 00:26:28,312
I'm not dissatisfied with anything. I live life carelessly.

785
00:26:28,313 --> 00:26:30,512
Right. Those around you become unhappy because of you.

786
00:26:30,513 --> 00:26:32,043
Correct. That's very true.

787
00:26:32,243 --> 00:26:36,113
That's why I was pretending to solve people's dissatisfaction.

788
00:26:36,213 --> 00:26:38,082
- I see.
- Since I wasn't the unhappy one.

789
00:26:38,083 --> 00:26:39,322
- It wasn't for you.
- No.

790
00:26:39,323 --> 00:26:41,352
With that, I thought,

791
00:26:41,353 --> 00:26:43,392
"Am I robbing opportunities from people like Sung Kyu..."

792
00:26:43,393 --> 00:26:46,763
"and Ji Young who desperately want to become announcers?"

793
00:26:47,333 --> 00:26:49,432
In a way, you had a guilty conscience.

794
00:26:49,433 --> 00:26:51,463
Yes, and so, I handed in my resignation letter.

795
00:26:51,803 --> 00:26:53,433
The director back then...

796
00:26:53,573 --> 00:26:55,832
suggested I take a short break.

797
00:26:55,833 --> 00:26:57,842
I grew weak hearing that,

798
00:26:57,843 --> 00:26:59,402
despite visiting him with determination.

799
00:26:59,403 --> 00:27:01,913
With that, I took a three-month leave of absence.

800
00:27:02,573 --> 00:27:05,643
During the 3 months, in the 1st month, I drank like crazy.

801
00:27:05,913 --> 00:27:08,152
In the second month, I helped my mom out...

802
00:27:08,153 --> 00:27:11,222
at her restaurant by doing the dishes...

803
00:27:11,223 --> 00:27:12,252
as I became self-conscious.

804
00:27:12,253 --> 00:27:16,423
In the last month, as I didn't want to return to work,

805
00:27:17,323 --> 00:27:18,393
I ran away...

806
00:27:18,593 --> 00:27:20,293
to the furthest country from Korea.

807
00:27:20,493 --> 00:27:22,262
I went to South America. Specifically, Argentina.

808
00:27:22,263 --> 00:27:23,762
- Abroad?
- To the very end.

809
00:27:23,763 --> 00:27:25,862
- To the other side.
- I didn't want to think at all.

810
00:27:25,863 --> 00:27:27,402
I simply ran away.

811
00:27:27,403 --> 00:27:29,873
I booked a departure and return flight,

812
00:27:30,073 --> 00:27:31,472
left the country as if running away,

813
00:27:31,473 --> 00:27:33,713
and toured South America for a month.

814
00:27:33,973 --> 00:27:34,973
That itself is amazing.

815
00:27:34,974 --> 00:27:36,342
- Near the end of my trip, - Yes?

816
00:27:36,343 --> 00:27:38,712
I had no money left in my bank account.

817
00:27:38,713 --> 00:27:39,952
- I see.
- You were...

818
00:27:39,953 --> 00:27:40,982
- broke.
- You had to work.

819
00:27:40,983 --> 00:27:43,082
That made me think, "How do I make a living?"

820
00:27:43,083 --> 00:27:45,082
"MBC is all I've got."

821
00:27:45,083 --> 00:27:46,382
- How realistic.
- Right?

822
00:27:46,383 --> 00:27:48,252
- If you're desperate...
- People start working hard...

823
00:27:48,253 --> 00:27:49,322
once they spend all the money...

824
00:27:49,323 --> 00:27:50,323
- Totally.
- loafing around.

825
00:27:50,324 --> 00:27:52,422
- I returned to work after that.
- That's interesting.

826
00:27:52,423 --> 00:27:53,662
But I had shifted my shows...

827
00:27:53,663 --> 00:27:55,033
- onto my colleagues.
- Right.

828
00:27:55,233 --> 00:27:57,402
Feeling bad about it, when I went back,

829
00:27:57,403 --> 00:28:01,572
I gifted perilla oil made from perilla seeds...

830
00:28:01,573 --> 00:28:03,032
that my dad harvested.

831
00:28:03,033 --> 00:28:05,643
Say that the one receiving it said, "I don't want it."

832
00:28:06,043 --> 00:28:08,043
- What would you have done?
- What?

833
00:28:08,313 --> 00:28:10,142
I would've been taken aback if that had happened.

834
00:28:10,143 --> 00:28:11,943
- It's you.
- That's how you talk to others.

835
00:28:12,083 --> 00:28:14,113
"I don't want it. I don't eat perilla oil."

836
00:28:14,683 --> 00:28:16,152
"Why are you giving it to me? I want sesame oil."

837
00:28:16,153 --> 00:28:17,282
"I only eat sesame oil."

838
00:28:17,283 --> 00:28:19,122
- "What's with this perilla oil?"
- "I don't need it."

839
00:28:19,123 --> 00:28:21,152
None of my colleagues were like that.

840
00:28:21,153 --> 00:28:23,722
- Is that so?
- Everyone welcomed me back.

841
00:28:23,723 --> 00:28:26,932
What shows are you known for?

842
00:28:26,933 --> 00:28:28,532
Rather than me being known for them,

843
00:28:28,533 --> 00:28:30,502
there are shows that MBC produced really well.

844
00:28:30,503 --> 00:28:32,762
- Right?
- Yes. There are "Consumer Reports,"

845
00:28:32,763 --> 00:28:34,802
news at different time slots,

846
00:28:34,803 --> 00:28:37,542
election coverage that MBC is known for, and more.

847
00:28:37,543 --> 00:28:38,802
Is it MBC when it comes to election coverage?

848
00:28:38,803 --> 00:28:40,072
- Of course, it's MBC.
- MBC.

849
00:28:40,073 --> 00:28:41,572
To say it's well known for...

850
00:28:41,573 --> 00:28:43,343
But JTBC's coverage is also good these days.

851
00:28:43,713 --> 00:28:44,713
What?

852
00:28:45,313 --> 00:28:46,612
- Are you willing to do it?
- What is he up to?

853
00:28:46,613 --> 00:28:47,652
- Stop it.
- What was that?

854
00:28:47,653 --> 00:28:49,412
- But JTBC has no plan...
- JTBC is good at it.

855
00:28:49,413 --> 00:28:50,652
- to cast you.
- Your social skills have improved.

856
00:28:50,653 --> 00:28:51,853
Yes, it's improving.

857
00:28:52,653 --> 00:28:54,992
- You're even praising him.
- You're practically a celebrity.

858
00:28:54,993 --> 00:28:56,722
Honestly,

859
00:28:56,723 --> 00:28:58,762
people only know you for "I Live Alone."

860
00:28:58,763 --> 00:29:00,962
"I Live Alone" is a blessing to me.

861
00:29:00,963 --> 00:29:03,262
But the show I love the most is the first one...

862
00:29:03,263 --> 00:29:04,703
I was assigned to after joining the company,

863
00:29:04,933 --> 00:29:07,132
"Share Happiness," which was a volunteer show.

864
00:29:07,133 --> 00:29:09,372
I learned a lot from that show.

865
00:29:09,373 --> 00:29:11,642
When you were on "I Live Alone,"

866
00:29:11,643 --> 00:29:13,473
you gained popularity.

867
00:29:13,613 --> 00:29:16,142
Couldn't that also have been when you realized that...

868
00:29:16,143 --> 00:29:18,483
working as a freelancer could be better for you?

869
00:29:18,643 --> 00:29:20,252
But I kept on working...

870
00:29:20,253 --> 00:29:21,352
even after I got on the show.

871
00:29:21,353 --> 00:29:22,711
I worked for about two more years.

872
00:29:23,510 --> 00:29:24,639
It was for the previous reason.

873
00:29:24,753 --> 00:29:26,793
It took me about two years...

874
00:29:27,089 --> 00:29:29,659
to pay back everything to MBC after returning.

875
00:29:29,780 --> 00:29:31,420
After finishing off with sports commentary,

876
00:29:31,746 --> 00:29:33,415
it felt like I had done my deed.

877
00:29:33,440 --> 00:29:35,069
- What you had in mind?
- When it felt like I had done...

878
00:29:35,094 --> 00:29:37,064
everything I owed, that's when I left.

879
00:29:37,603 --> 00:29:39,402
You might have thought that it was enough,

880
00:29:39,403 --> 00:29:41,772
but MBC might not have felt that way.

881
00:29:41,773 --> 00:29:44,043
That doesn't matter.

882
00:29:44,873 --> 00:29:46,242
He's very sure of himself.

883
00:29:46,243 --> 00:29:47,512
- He is.
- Yes.

884
00:29:47,513 --> 00:29:49,212
- He's very sure.
- "It's my life."

885
00:29:49,213 --> 00:29:51,342
- It was what I felt.
- "It's my life."

886
00:29:51,343 --> 00:29:52,512
- That's important.
- I'm like that, too.

887
00:29:52,513 --> 00:29:54,152
If I say it’s cleared, it’s cleared.

888
00:29:54,153 --> 00:29:56,582
- Yes, it's your own life.
- Sure. I was done.

889
00:29:56,583 --> 00:29:58,552
Did you move, or did you always live in Yangpyeong?

890
00:29:58,553 --> 00:30:00,522
I was born in Gaegun-myeon, Yangpyeong.

891
00:30:00,523 --> 00:30:03,122
Then I moved to Ansan for a bit because of my father's work.

892
00:30:03,123 --> 00:30:04,723
You're not like someone from Gaegun-myeon.

893
00:30:06,123 --> 00:30:08,163
We always share, think of others,

894
00:30:08,663 --> 00:30:10,132
and praise others no matter what.

895
00:30:10,133 --> 00:30:12,132
- He only shares shows.
- Sure.

896
00:30:12,133 --> 00:30:13,802
And he said his favorite show...

897
00:30:13,803 --> 00:30:15,572
was "Share Happiness."

898
00:30:15,573 --> 00:30:16,902
- It doesn't match.
- Gosh.

899
00:30:16,903 --> 00:30:18,102
He seems so fake.

900
00:30:18,103 --> 00:30:19,902
- This is so hard.
- That's what he said.

901
00:30:19,903 --> 00:30:21,072
There’s no consistency.

902
00:30:21,073 --> 00:30:23,783
- And it doesn’t add up.
- Next, Kwaktube.

903
00:30:24,083 --> 00:30:26,442
Kwaktube wrote, "Embassy personnel."

904
00:30:26,443 --> 00:30:28,212
- That's what he said.
- You used to work for the embassy?

905
00:30:28,213 --> 00:30:31,382
I was a staff officer at the Korean Embassy in Azerbaijan.

906
00:30:31,383 --> 00:30:33,252
How old were you when you first started?

907
00:30:33,253 --> 00:30:37,122
I was 27 or 28 when I...

908
00:30:37,123 --> 00:30:39,322
- That was your first job?
- No, it wasn't.

909
00:30:39,323 --> 00:30:40,993
I used to work for a Russian trade company.

910
00:30:41,763 --> 00:30:43,502
I realized that it wasn't my thing.

911
00:30:43,503 --> 00:30:45,232
- That's amazing.
- I thought I had that bad job...

912
00:30:45,233 --> 00:30:47,672
because my English skills were lacking,

913
00:30:47,673 --> 00:30:49,932
so I went to Ireland on my own to study English.

914
00:30:49,933 --> 00:30:51,802
I studied for about nine months,

915
00:30:51,803 --> 00:30:55,042
and I applied for the embassy while I was there and got in.

916
00:30:55,043 --> 00:30:57,742
I thought I was underqualified for the embassy,

917
00:30:57,743 --> 00:31:00,383
but I got accepted and I cried so much.

918
00:31:00,753 --> 00:31:03,182
It was near Parents' Day,

919
00:31:03,183 --> 00:31:05,222
and the embassy sent flowers to my parents.

920
00:31:05,223 --> 00:31:06,682
- Gosh.
- Really?

921
00:31:06,683 --> 00:31:10,092
Not just for the new hires, but all employees.

922
00:31:10,093 --> 00:31:11,923
My mom saw that and cried as well.

923
00:31:12,123 --> 00:31:13,392
Sure, she must have been proud.

924
00:31:13,393 --> 00:31:16,292
Was the reason why they hired you...

925
00:31:16,293 --> 00:31:18,032
because you had the language skills?

926
00:31:18,033 --> 00:31:20,672
- I majored in Russian, - Yes.

927
00:31:20,673 --> 00:31:22,302
so I knew how to speak Russian,

928
00:31:22,303 --> 00:31:25,243
but later on, I heard that I came in last on the Russian test.

929
00:31:26,343 --> 00:31:27,743
But I did well in the interview.

930
00:31:28,473 --> 00:31:30,842
- It was because...
- You just need to speak well.

931
00:31:30,843 --> 00:31:33,782
- Who cares about test results?
- It's just conversational level.

932
00:31:33,783 --> 00:31:36,252
What did they like about you?

933
00:31:36,253 --> 00:31:37,722
I heard this later on when we were closer,

934
00:31:37,723 --> 00:31:40,352
but they said that I seemed very smooth and easygoing.

935
00:31:40,353 --> 00:31:42,453
But actually, I had just given up hope.

936
00:31:42,793 --> 00:31:43,793
I didn't expect to get accepted.

937
00:31:43,794 --> 00:31:44,992
Sure. You were about to give up.

938
00:31:44,993 --> 00:31:46,092
So you didn't get nervous and took it easy?

939
00:31:46,093 --> 00:31:47,662
I just took it easy, and I was just about to give up...

940
00:31:47,663 --> 00:31:49,263
and become a tour guide.

941
00:31:49,533 --> 00:31:51,702
But it turned out well, and I got in.

942
00:31:51,703 --> 00:31:54,202
The reason I started studying a foreign language was because...

943
00:31:54,203 --> 00:31:55,902
I loved foreign football leagues.

944
00:31:55,903 --> 00:31:57,142
Kyung Hoon also likes soccer.

945
00:31:57,143 --> 00:31:58,602
I wanted to watch the games,

946
00:31:58,603 --> 00:31:59,872
but we didn't have money at home,

947
00:31:59,873 --> 00:32:01,742
so going to watch the games seemed like a luxury.

948
00:32:01,743 --> 00:32:05,713
I thought I could watch them for free if I became an interpreter.

949
00:32:06,513 --> 00:32:08,652
- That's thinking outside the box.
- Yes.

950
00:32:08,653 --> 00:32:11,383
I applied for Spanish and German,

951
00:32:11,923 --> 00:32:12,952
but I didn't get accepted.

952
00:32:12,953 --> 00:32:15,492
Russian was my third choice, and I got in.

953
00:32:15,493 --> 00:32:16,652
- That's amazing.
- Is that why?

954
00:32:16,653 --> 00:32:18,062
How many languages do you speak now?

955
00:32:18,063 --> 00:32:20,592
Conversationally, I can speak three languages.

956
00:32:20,593 --> 00:32:22,192
Korean, English, and Russian.

957
00:32:22,193 --> 00:32:24,832
For basic travel use,

958
00:32:24,833 --> 00:32:27,002
I can also speak Japanese and Spanish.

959
00:32:27,003 --> 00:32:28,032
- When he goes abroad, - Really?

960
00:32:28,033 --> 00:32:30,072
- he can just speak right away.
- It just comes out.

961
00:32:30,073 --> 00:32:31,502
He's naturally gifted with languages.

962
00:32:31,503 --> 00:32:32,743
He can speak five languages.

963
00:32:33,103 --> 00:32:38,313
(Korean to Russian)

964
00:32:38,643 --> 00:32:42,182
(Korean to English)

965
00:32:42,183 --> 00:32:45,723
(Korean to English)

966
00:32:46,123 --> 00:32:52,492
(Korean to Japanese)

967
00:32:52,493 --> 00:32:54,792
Kwaktube, some people say that...

968
00:32:54,793 --> 00:32:56,532
the employees at the embassy can be unfriendly.

969
00:32:56,533 --> 00:32:58,462
I'm sure the employees at the embassy...

970
00:32:58,463 --> 00:33:00,403
have their point of view.

971
00:33:00,803 --> 00:33:03,332
Well, I didn't work for the team that handled complaints,

972
00:33:03,333 --> 00:33:06,143
so I'm not exactly sure about their difficulties.

973
00:33:06,343 --> 00:33:08,542
But I was in Azerbaijan,

974
00:33:08,543 --> 00:33:10,712
and we didn't have many tourists. Not many Koreans visited,

975
00:33:10,713 --> 00:33:12,482
so we had fewer complaints than other countries.

976
00:33:12,483 --> 00:33:14,952
But most of the complaints filed are for lost passports,

977
00:33:14,953 --> 00:33:16,712
and if they were unfriendly,

978
00:33:16,713 --> 00:33:18,482
then it could be because there are a lot of...

979
00:33:18,483 --> 00:33:21,292
lost passports since there are more tourists in that country.

980
00:33:21,293 --> 00:33:22,922
They have more incidents, to begin with.

981
00:33:22,923 --> 00:33:24,962
We have to take care of phone call duties as well,

982
00:33:24,963 --> 00:33:26,862
- and we get calls at 3am or 4am...
- That must be hard.

983
00:33:26,863 --> 00:33:28,292
from people asking for tourist sites...

984
00:33:28,293 --> 00:33:29,732
- or restaurant recommendations - Those kinds of phone calls?

985
00:33:29,733 --> 00:33:31,262
- Those kinds of phone calls?
- They do that?

986
00:33:31,263 --> 00:33:33,102
- Really?
- Since we are at the embassy,

987
00:33:33,103 --> 00:33:34,872
we know the place very well.

988
00:33:34,873 --> 00:33:36,432
But why would they ask...

989
00:33:36,433 --> 00:33:37,742
- the embassy for recommendations?
- I know.

990
00:33:37,743 --> 00:33:38,872
- There are people who confuse...
- Are there people like that?

991
00:33:38,873 --> 00:33:40,813
the embassy with the tourism office.

992
00:33:41,913 --> 00:33:43,682
There are people who think that...

993
00:33:43,683 --> 00:33:45,212
we are the information center at the tourism office.

994
00:33:45,213 --> 00:33:46,642
That happens sometimes.

995
00:33:46,643 --> 00:33:48,982
You need to take calls in the middle of the night?

996
00:33:48,983 --> 00:33:51,352
- They do.
- It's mandated by law.

997
00:33:51,353 --> 00:33:52,852
- It's mandated?
- So those on duty...

998
00:33:52,853 --> 00:33:54,822
- take care of it.
- That must be so tough.

999
00:33:54,823 --> 00:33:57,222
Didn't you lose your passport while you were traveling, Kyung Hoon?

1000
00:33:57,223 --> 00:33:58,223
Yes, when I was in Switzerland.

1001
00:33:58,224 --> 00:33:59,963
- Yes, what happened?
- Why did you go to Switzerland?

1002
00:34:00,163 --> 00:34:01,992
- My honeymoon.
- His honeymoon.

1003
00:34:01,993 --> 00:34:03,662
- Hey!
- It was his honeymoon.

1004
00:34:03,663 --> 00:34:06,162
How would I know where he went for his honeymoon?

1005
00:34:06,163 --> 00:34:07,932
- He told us.
- He told us so many times.

1006
00:34:07,933 --> 00:34:09,732
- How many times?
- Pay some attention...

1007
00:34:09,733 --> 00:34:10,902
- to those around you.
- Did you know?

1008
00:34:10,903 --> 00:34:12,672
He told us 7,000 times.

1009
00:34:12,673 --> 00:34:13,942
You went to Switzerland?

1010
00:34:13,943 --> 00:34:15,642
Please, you heartless man.

1011
00:34:15,643 --> 00:34:16,672
It's my first time hearing that.

1012
00:34:16,673 --> 00:34:18,742
- He told us.
- Give others some love.

1013
00:34:18,743 --> 00:34:20,612
Why did you go all the way to Switzerland?

1014
00:34:20,613 --> 00:34:21,882
It was our honeymoon.

1015
00:34:21,883 --> 00:34:23,882
Whatever you say back and forth, it's Switzerland.

1016
00:34:23,883 --> 00:34:26,122
- Don't you even remember?
- I had no idea.

1017
00:34:26,123 --> 00:34:27,222
So, what did you do?

1018
00:34:27,223 --> 00:34:28,692
- What did you do when you lost it?
- Well,

1019
00:34:28,693 --> 00:34:30,762
I contacted the place where I lost it,

1020
00:34:30,763 --> 00:34:32,162
and I got it the next day.

1021
00:34:32,163 --> 00:34:33,662
The cleaning staff found it.

1022
00:34:33,663 --> 00:34:35,562
- They found it?
- They gave it to me.

1023
00:34:35,563 --> 00:34:37,462
- So I was very grateful.
- Your wife can speak English.

1024
00:34:37,463 --> 00:34:39,032
- Yes.
- You would have never managed.

1025
00:34:39,033 --> 00:34:40,233
I tried my best as well.

1026
00:34:41,003 --> 00:34:43,132
- He studied English.
- I had to find it.

1027
00:34:43,133 --> 00:34:44,542
It must be hard to work at the embassy.

1028
00:34:44,543 --> 00:34:47,442
Let's move on to the current jobs.

1029
00:34:47,443 --> 00:34:50,712
Dae Ho wrote "Celebrity."

1030
00:34:50,713 --> 00:34:52,682
Do you see yourself as a celebrity?

1031
00:34:52,683 --> 00:34:53,782
Just a celebrity.

1032
00:34:53,783 --> 00:34:55,653
Aren’t announcers celebrities?

1033
00:34:55,953 --> 00:34:58,582
There are different words for announcers,

1034
00:34:58,583 --> 00:34:59,852
but we are usually seen as journalists.

1035
00:34:59,853 --> 00:35:01,692
- Journalists?
- Journalists.

1036
00:35:01,693 --> 00:35:03,992
How is life as a celebrity...

1037
00:35:03,993 --> 00:35:05,122
since you used to be a journalist?

1038
00:35:05,123 --> 00:35:06,223
I made the right choice.

1039
00:35:06,863 --> 00:35:08,793
- Does it suit you well?
- After transitioning to this,

1040
00:35:08,963 --> 00:35:11,902
I’ve made new connections,

1041
00:35:11,903 --> 00:35:15,372
and I'm discovering unexpected enjoyment.

1042
00:35:15,373 --> 00:35:18,002
Dae Ho, for us singers,

1043
00:35:18,003 --> 00:35:19,302
when we sign a contract with our agencies,

1044
00:35:19,303 --> 00:35:21,172
the albums and concerts...

1045
00:35:21,173 --> 00:35:23,442
- Sure.
- are also included in the terms.

1046
00:35:23,443 --> 00:35:26,682
For you, what are the conditions?

1047
00:35:26,683 --> 00:35:27,852
When you signed with Soo Geun.

1048
00:35:27,853 --> 00:35:28,853
It's probably his life.

1049
00:35:30,053 --> 00:35:31,682
- With a blood oath?
- That question...

1050
00:35:31,683 --> 00:35:33,422
- That question was a good one.
- What else does he need?

1051
00:35:33,423 --> 00:35:36,222
- For entertainment.
- Like that?

1052
00:35:36,223 --> 00:35:37,463
With a blood oath?

1053
00:35:37,623 --> 00:35:39,292
- Sure.
- He makes a pinky promise.

1054
00:35:39,293 --> 00:35:40,693
That's it.

1055
00:35:41,193 --> 00:35:42,862
Among the people you met after becoming a celebrity,

1056
00:35:42,863 --> 00:35:44,102
who was the most unbelievable one?

1057
00:35:44,103 --> 00:35:45,232
- The most memorable.
- For me,

1058
00:35:45,233 --> 00:35:47,103
seeing female celebrities is always fun.

1059
00:35:47,703 --> 00:35:48,703
He's honest.

1060
00:35:48,704 --> 00:35:50,503
Who was the prettiest?

1061
00:35:50,673 --> 00:35:52,003
- Ha Ji Won was so charming.
- Really?

1062
00:35:53,143 --> 00:35:54,972
- Ha Ji Won was so charming.
- She's so pretty.

1063
00:35:54,973 --> 00:35:56,912
I also met Yoo In Young not long ago,

1064
00:35:56,913 --> 00:35:58,382
and she was also very charming.

1065
00:35:58,383 --> 00:35:59,713
You're close with her, Yeong Cheol.

1066
00:36:00,013 --> 00:36:01,953
I have plans with her next month. Do you want to join us?

1067
00:36:03,353 --> 00:36:04,652
I'll show you how celebrities hang.

1068
00:36:04,653 --> 00:36:06,152
- You really are a celebrity.
- Celebrities...

1069
00:36:06,153 --> 00:36:08,052
- Real celebrities drink champagne.
- Yeong Cheol.

1070
00:36:08,053 --> 00:36:09,352
Yeong Cheol.

1071
00:36:09,353 --> 00:36:12,123
I'm sorry, but why do you have plans with Yoo In Young?

1072
00:36:12,463 --> 00:36:13,692
- Yes.
- I'm close friends with her.

1073
00:36:13,693 --> 00:36:15,362
- Are you sure it's not Yoo In Won?
- Why?

1074
00:36:15,363 --> 00:36:17,502
But if you're friends with Yeong Cheol,

1075
00:36:17,503 --> 00:36:20,362
you go to fancy restaurants.

1076
00:36:20,363 --> 00:36:21,572
- That must be nice.
- Yes.

1077
00:36:21,573 --> 00:36:23,433
Do you know what fine dining is, Dae Ho?

1078
00:36:23,803 --> 00:36:25,542
I'll just meet up with her separately.

1079
00:36:25,543 --> 00:36:27,312
What do you mean? Fine dining.

1080
00:36:27,313 --> 00:36:29,272
Don't you want to try Michelin restaurants?

1081
00:36:29,273 --> 00:36:30,812
- Michelin restaurants?
- Do you pay, Yeong Cheol?

1082
00:36:30,813 --> 00:36:31,912
Or do you go Dutch?

1083
00:36:31,913 --> 00:36:32,913
Dutch.

1084
00:36:32,914 --> 00:36:34,313
(Real Celebrity)

1085
00:36:34,583 --> 00:36:35,912
Yeong Cheol pays.

1086
00:36:35,913 --> 00:36:36,913
- Yeong Cheol pays.
- I'll pay.

1087
00:36:36,914 --> 00:36:38,152
- I'll pay.
- Dae Ho.

1088
00:36:38,177 --> 00:36:40,830
Have you ever done an event without telling your agency?

1089
00:36:41,393 --> 00:36:42,792
- I've never done it in secret.
- You haven't?

1090
00:36:42,793 --> 00:36:44,492
Shall we listen to your story, Kyung Hoon?

1091
00:36:44,493 --> 00:36:45,493
What?

1092
00:36:45,993 --> 00:36:47,792
You must have done something...

1093
00:36:47,793 --> 00:36:48,862
- without telling your agency.
- Did you?

1094
00:36:48,863 --> 00:36:50,702
- If I go, everyone knows.
- Hey.

1095
00:36:50,703 --> 00:36:52,462
Everyone finds out. I can't do that.

1096
00:36:52,463 --> 00:36:53,562
He can't do that.

1097
00:36:53,563 --> 00:36:55,202
- We will all get caught.
- Yes, we will get caught.

1098
00:36:55,203 --> 00:36:56,632
- They take pictures.
- For sure.

1099
00:36:56,633 --> 00:36:58,473
We need to submit an approval form.

1100
00:36:58,743 --> 00:37:00,472
From the cost,

1101
00:37:00,473 --> 00:37:02,472
- when it is, for how long, - Sure.

1102
00:37:02,473 --> 00:37:03,782
- what kind of event it is, - Really?

1103
00:37:03,783 --> 00:37:04,942
and who is holding it.

1104
00:37:04,943 --> 00:37:06,142
You can apply, though?

1105
00:37:06,143 --> 00:37:08,482
If it's a non-profit event and held by a government institution,

1106
00:37:08,483 --> 00:37:09,752
or a public corporation.

1107
00:37:09,753 --> 00:37:11,582
When you get paid for that,

1108
00:37:11,583 --> 00:37:13,182
is that all yours?

1109
00:37:13,183 --> 00:37:16,522
I think I got the entire pay.

1110
00:37:16,523 --> 00:37:19,562
It's usually through an official procedure,

1111
00:37:19,563 --> 00:37:20,692
so I let the agency know.

1112
00:37:20,693 --> 00:37:22,092
When you decided to become a freelancer,

1113
00:37:22,093 --> 00:37:24,932
you must have agonized over it deeply.

1114
00:37:24,933 --> 00:37:26,932
Right before you made the decision,

1115
00:37:26,933 --> 00:37:28,903
what was the biggest concern for you?

1116
00:37:30,033 --> 00:37:31,742
I don't think I had any big concerns...

1117
00:37:31,743 --> 00:37:33,302
before leaving the company.

1118
00:37:33,303 --> 00:37:35,112
Because I did my best...

1119
00:37:35,113 --> 00:37:36,313
(Gosh)

1120
00:37:36,513 --> 00:37:38,012
- That's not what he wanted.
- That's not it.

1121
00:37:38,013 --> 00:37:39,983
He worked hard for two years.

1122
00:37:40,513 --> 00:37:41,513
What a rotten question.

1123
00:37:41,514 --> 00:37:43,082
He did everything he could.

1124
00:37:43,083 --> 00:37:44,953
- What a rotten question.
- Gosh, that hurts.

1125
00:37:45,123 --> 00:37:47,152
So fresh.

1126
00:37:47,153 --> 00:37:49,152
The question itself was wrong.

1127
00:37:49,153 --> 00:37:50,562
I almost broke my rib.

1128
00:37:50,563 --> 00:37:52,322
Come on.

1129
00:37:52,323 --> 00:37:53,323
- He said...
- They are not...

1130
00:37:53,324 --> 00:37:55,333
- They are not a good match.
- Totally incompatible.

1131
00:37:55,833 --> 00:37:57,603
I will try again.

1132
00:37:58,533 --> 00:38:00,002
You need to give me the right question.

1133
00:38:00,003 --> 00:38:01,973
- You became a freelancer.
- Yes.

1134
00:38:02,573 --> 00:38:07,003
The expectations of people always end up becoming a burden.

1135
00:38:07,413 --> 00:38:09,413
- Right?
- I didn't feel any burden.

1136
00:38:09,513 --> 00:38:11,142
(My ribs...)

1137
00:38:11,143 --> 00:38:13,182
- That hurts.
- They don't get along.

1138
00:38:13,183 --> 00:38:14,352
- He did his best.
- That hurts.

1139
00:38:14,353 --> 00:38:16,452
- I didn't feel any burden.
- He didn't.

1140
00:38:16,453 --> 00:38:18,452
The expectations didn't pressure you?

1141
00:38:18,453 --> 00:38:20,522
- No burden?
- I had done my best.

1142
00:38:20,523 --> 00:38:22,852
Then, let's put it this way.

1143
00:38:22,853 --> 00:38:24,222
How long has it been now?

1144
00:38:24,223 --> 00:38:26,292
- About 7 or 8 months?
- About 10 months.

1145
00:38:26,293 --> 00:38:29,833
Out of 100, how would you rate Freelancer Kim Dae Ho?

1146
00:38:30,293 --> 00:38:31,303
What score?

1147
00:38:32,133 --> 00:38:33,563
Out of 100?

1148
00:38:34,233 --> 00:38:37,132
Up until recently, I would have said 80,

1149
00:38:37,133 --> 00:38:38,203
but now,

1150
00:38:38,543 --> 00:38:39,572
I'm back to zero.

1151
00:38:39,573 --> 00:38:40,972
- What? Why?
- Yes.

1152
00:38:40,973 --> 00:38:43,812
- Why is it zero?
- I think I was overly rushed...

1153
00:38:43,813 --> 00:38:47,013
and made myself think that I was doing the right thing.

1154
00:38:47,283 --> 00:38:48,652
But not long ago, I realized that...

1155
00:38:48,653 --> 00:38:51,723
I tried to replace my image as a news anchor so much.

1156
00:38:52,153 --> 00:38:55,153
But for 14 years, my experience as a news anchor...

1157
00:38:55,293 --> 00:38:57,862
- was like the skin on my face.
- Right.

1158
00:38:57,863 --> 00:39:00,323
I figured I shouldn't have to replace this...

1159
00:39:00,493 --> 00:39:02,263
- but just combine it well instead.
- That's right.

1160
00:39:02,493 --> 00:39:06,162
- So, I'm starting over from zero.
- You're starting over?

1161
00:39:06,163 --> 00:39:10,132
There have been quite a few news anchors who became freelancers.

1162
00:39:10,133 --> 00:39:11,242
- Lots of them.
- Yes.

1163
00:39:11,243 --> 00:39:13,203
Do you consider yourself...

1164
00:39:13,503 --> 00:39:15,443
among the top three in Korea?

1165
00:39:15,643 --> 00:39:17,213
- I'm sure he is.
- The top three in your mind.

1166
00:39:17,743 --> 00:39:19,083
We may be in different positions,

1167
00:39:19,643 --> 00:39:22,312
but in this situation, taking into account many objective...

1168
00:39:22,313 --> 00:39:23,983
and overall views, I am.

1169
00:39:25,223 --> 00:39:27,053
- You're in the top 3?
- You think you're in the top 3?

1170
00:39:27,293 --> 00:39:28,492
- In the top three?
- Hey, what are you talking about?

1171
00:39:28,493 --> 00:39:29,822
There's Jang Ye Won.

1172
00:39:29,823 --> 00:39:31,362
- Hey, but...
- I mean, there's Kim Seong Ju.

1173
00:39:31,363 --> 00:39:33,192
- There's Jun Hyun Moo.
- Right, Jun Hyun Moo.

1174
00:39:33,193 --> 00:39:34,833
- Hyun Moo and Seong Ju are...
- Sung Kyu.

1175
00:39:35,133 --> 00:39:36,662
- You name them. The top three.
- And Do Kyung Wan.

1176
00:39:36,663 --> 00:39:38,462
- The top three in your mind.
- Jo Woo Jong. There are so many.

1177
00:39:38,463 --> 00:39:39,903
- Jun Hyun Moo.
- Jun Hyun Moo.

1178
00:39:40,063 --> 00:39:41,432
- Kim Seong Ju.
- Kim Seong Ju.

1179
00:39:41,433 --> 00:39:42,502
Me.

1180
00:39:42,503 --> 00:39:43,503
(Top 3 news anchors according to Dae Ho: Jun Hyun Moo, Kim Seong Ju, Me)

1181
00:39:43,903 --> 00:39:46,102
(Everyone applauds.)

1182
00:39:46,103 --> 00:39:47,613
You asked me my opinion.

1183
00:39:47,813 --> 00:39:49,072
- Right.
- That's true.

1184
00:39:49,073 --> 00:39:50,982
- Others might think differently.
- Well, sure.

1185
00:39:50,983 --> 00:39:52,313
What about Jang Sung Kyu?

1186
00:39:52,583 --> 00:39:53,683
My friend, Jang Sung Kyu.

1187
00:39:53,783 --> 00:39:56,352
Sung Kyu's rank is different based on timing,

1188
00:39:56,353 --> 00:39:57,482
but right now, I'm higher.

1189
00:39:57,483 --> 00:39:59,182
- Oh, he fluctuates a bit?
- Yes, he does.

1190
00:39:59,183 --> 00:40:01,622
- Who else is there?
- Dae Ho's ranking is so refreshing.

1191
00:40:01,623 --> 00:40:03,622
- Well, but...
- He gave himself zero points,

1192
00:40:03,623 --> 00:40:04,762
but he's in the top three.

1193
00:40:04,763 --> 00:40:06,163
(Still in the Top 3)

1194
00:40:06,963 --> 00:40:08,433
- Gosh, this is...
- When I am...

1195
00:40:08,463 --> 00:40:09,962
- Then...
- I rise to 100 points...

1196
00:40:09,963 --> 00:40:11,533
Gosh, you're so scary!

1197
00:40:12,033 --> 00:40:15,102
Then, what was his rank when he scored himself at 80 points?

1198
00:40:15,103 --> 00:40:16,532
- You must've been number one.
- Of course.

1199
00:40:16,533 --> 00:40:18,072
- Gosh, back then, the timing...
- Practically Conan O'Brien.

1200
00:40:18,073 --> 00:40:19,843
- It was different.
- Were you number one?

1201
00:40:19,903 --> 00:40:21,312
- Back then? No.
- When you did your best.

1202
00:40:21,313 --> 00:40:22,613
- I was never number one.
- Well, that is...

1203
00:40:22,773 --> 00:40:24,943
Were you ever number two?

1204
00:40:25,213 --> 00:40:26,743
I was off and on.

1205
00:40:27,113 --> 00:40:28,152
(Bravo, Kim Dae Ho!)

1206
00:40:28,153 --> 00:40:29,283
Bravo!

1207
00:40:29,913 --> 00:40:31,953
People from Yangpyeong are honest.

1208
00:40:32,383 --> 00:40:34,422
- He just says it out loud.
- No, I like it.

1209
00:40:34,423 --> 00:40:36,792
Next, it's Kwaktube. Your current job is a YouTuber.

1210
00:40:36,793 --> 00:40:38,192
You have over two million subscribers now, right?

1211
00:40:38,193 --> 00:40:39,593
