00:48:40,103 --> 00:48:41,912
it's been a while since we did this.

1443
00:48:41,913 --> 00:48:44,113
- What is it?
- The transfer students picked...

1444
00:48:44,143 --> 00:48:46,842
someone among us whom they wanted as an older brother.

1445
00:48:46,843 --> 00:48:48,383
It's like choosing the person they want to be paired with.

1446
00:48:49,283 --> 00:48:51,552
Dae Ho wrote Hee Chul.

1447
00:48:51,553 --> 00:48:54,082
- What?
- He wrote Hee Chul.

1448
00:48:54,083 --> 00:48:55,493
It's very unexpected.

1449
00:48:55,793 --> 00:48:57,693
It's very unexpected. Why?

1450
00:48:58,123 --> 00:48:59,363
I just...

1451
00:48:59,393 --> 00:49:01,763
Since I'm an older brother,

1452
00:49:01,933 --> 00:49:03,262
I don't really want an older brother.

1453
00:49:03,263 --> 00:49:04,933
An older brother...

1454
00:49:05,433 --> 00:49:07,463
- He has a certain mind.
- An older brother...

1455
00:49:08,433 --> 00:49:11,272
Younger siblings grow up while looking up to their older brother.

1456
00:49:11,273 --> 00:49:14,772
I try to live like that even now.

1457
00:49:14,773 --> 00:49:17,572
I want to live like Peter Pan.

1458
00:49:17,573 --> 00:49:18,613
He's immature?

1459
00:49:18,783 --> 00:49:19,843
Immature.

1460
00:49:20,313 --> 00:49:22,152
He thinks I live however I want the most recklessly.

1461
00:49:22,153 --> 00:49:24,783
He lives a cool life with responsibility.

1462
00:49:24,983 --> 00:49:26,983
That's how I want to live. Freely.

1463
00:49:27,083 --> 00:49:29,092
- Come...
- He still has his own rules.

1464
00:49:29,093 --> 00:49:30,452
- That's right.
- Come hang out on the 28th.

1465
00:49:30,453 --> 00:49:33,023
Kian84 and Calm Down Man will be there. Come and hang.

1466
00:49:33,363 --> 00:49:34,493
I'll see if I have time.

1467
00:49:36,663 --> 00:49:37,663
"I'll see if I have time."

1468
00:49:37,664 --> 00:49:38,863
(In awe)

1469
00:49:39,163 --> 00:49:41,232
I might have something too.

1470
00:49:41,233 --> 00:49:43,373
- He has to be consistent.
- Right.

1471
00:49:43,473 --> 00:49:46,373
Joon Bin's choice...

1472
00:49:46,643 --> 00:49:48,442
- was Hee Chul as well.
- Really?

1473
00:49:48,443 --> 00:49:49,972
- Me?
- A double champion.

1474
00:49:49,973 --> 00:49:51,482
You're the big brother...

1475
00:49:51,483 --> 00:49:52,943
- among those born in the 1980s.
- Here, I'm...

1476
00:49:53,043 --> 00:49:54,982
I'm the king among those born in the 1980s.

1477
00:49:54,983 --> 00:49:56,013
(An icon for those born in the 1980s)

1478
00:49:56,153 --> 00:49:58,422
- We have many mutual friends.
- That's right.

1479
00:49:58,423 --> 00:50:00,982
He goes to many gatherings with his close friends.

1480
00:50:00,983 --> 00:50:02,992
He also spends a lot on games. I could relate to that.

1481
00:50:02,993 --> 00:50:05,062
- He spends a lot.
- I'm usually ranked 1st or 2nd...

1482
00:50:05,063 --> 00:50:06,823
in the game I play.

1483
00:50:07,293 --> 00:50:09,493
You have to get it together now.

1484
00:50:09,693 --> 00:50:11,862
- You should come back to reality.
- That's what...

1485
00:50:11,863 --> 00:50:13,732
That's what I don't want to hear.

1486
00:50:13,733 --> 00:50:15,573
Come and hang on the 28th.

1487
00:50:15,673 --> 00:50:16,772
Then...

1488
00:50:16,773 --> 00:50:19,942
This is the last item for the transfer students.

1489
00:50:19,943 --> 00:50:21,672
We sometimes want to do this.

1490
00:50:21,673 --> 00:50:23,072
Guess Who I Am.

1491
00:50:23,073 --> 00:50:24,442
It's been a while.

1492
00:50:24,443 --> 00:50:26,282
- Let's go!
- Let's go.

1493
00:50:26,283 --> 00:50:28,383
(Transfer Student Quiz, Guess Who I Am)

1494
00:50:28,553 --> 00:50:30,113
- I'll give you the quiz.
- Okay.

1495
00:50:30,253 --> 00:50:31,582
If you guess it wrong,

1496
00:50:31,583 --> 00:50:32,953
- you get hit by the toy hammer.
- I think he'll hit us hard.

1497
00:50:33,183 --> 00:50:34,253
I think my head will spin.

1498
00:50:34,993 --> 00:50:36,352
- Watch him.
- That's not true.

1499
00:50:36,353 --> 00:50:37,652
- It's going to be scary.
- I think he'll hit you really hard.

1500
00:50:37,653 --> 00:50:39,722
In 2011,

1501
00:50:39,723 --> 00:50:42,492
I was hired through an audition program called "New Employee."

1502
00:50:42,493 --> 00:50:44,432
As part of my main role as an announcer,

1503
00:50:44,433 --> 00:50:46,402
I worked on both TV and radio news.

1504
00:50:46,403 --> 00:50:48,432
There was a time I made a mistake...

1505
00:50:48,433 --> 00:50:51,542
during the news broadcast. What was the mistake?

1506
00:50:51,543 --> 00:50:54,073
There are famous international athletes.

1507
00:50:54,103 --> 00:50:56,673
Their names would mean something nice in their country,

1508
00:50:56,813 --> 00:50:58,913
but when translated into Korean...

1509
00:50:59,283 --> 00:51:00,942
- For example...
- Shibasaki.

1510
00:51:00,943 --> 00:51:02,582
- Shibasaki.
- Shibasaki.

1511
00:51:02,583 --> 00:51:04,582
- Foreign athletes like that.
- Right.

1512
00:51:04,583 --> 00:51:07,722
When pronounced in the Korean way, it may sound...

1513
00:51:07,723 --> 00:51:09,492
- Like an insult.
- It may sound like that.

1514
00:51:09,493 --> 00:51:11,253
- That's right.
- You messed up on live TV.

1515
00:51:11,463 --> 00:51:12,993
That sometimes happens,

1516
00:51:13,693 --> 00:51:15,363
but it wasn't my case.

1517
00:51:15,763 --> 00:51:17,532
- What was your case?
- What?

1518
00:51:17,533 --> 00:51:18,602
Your case.

1519
00:51:18,603 --> 00:51:19,662
- We...
- You'd know better than us.

1520
00:51:19,663 --> 00:51:22,103
- He wouldn't know.
- usually do live broadcasts,

1521
00:51:22,233 --> 00:51:23,872
so there's a camera in front,

1522
00:51:23,873 --> 00:51:25,803
and there's a script as well.

1523
00:51:26,243 --> 00:51:28,812
Also, there's a prompter in front.

1524
00:51:28,813 --> 00:51:30,442
- That's right.
- We read the words...

1525
00:51:30,443 --> 00:51:31,883
like looking at a Magic Eye picture,

1526
00:51:32,143 --> 00:51:33,682
but it looks like we're looking...

1527
00:51:33,683 --> 00:51:35,183
- at the camera.
- Right.

1528
00:51:35,283 --> 00:51:38,483
So our eyes don't move so much.

1529
00:51:38,583 --> 00:51:41,123
- Right.
- We're just reading the text.

1530
00:51:41,423 --> 00:51:43,123
I made a mistake while doing that.

1531
00:51:43,493 --> 00:51:44,793
- Really?
- I know.

1532
00:51:45,093 --> 00:51:48,362
Dae Ho is honest in talking about his inner feelings.

1533
00:51:48,363 --> 00:51:50,063
So the text...

1534
00:51:50,293 --> 00:51:53,402
was something like congratulating the 85th Anniversary of Liberation,

1535
00:51:53,403 --> 00:51:56,403
but you said to yourself, "I don't congratulate it."

1536
00:51:57,433 --> 00:51:59,002
- You...
- Right.

1537
00:51:59,003 --> 00:52:01,143
- spoke your mind.
- I wasn't going to hit you...

1538
00:52:01,943 --> 00:52:03,012
He...

1539
00:52:03,013 --> 00:52:05,182
You don't even celebrate the liberation?

1540
00:52:05,183 --> 00:52:07,042
You're really mean. You didn't celebrate the liberation?

1541
00:52:07,043 --> 00:52:08,382
Long live Korea!

1542
00:52:08,383 --> 00:52:10,213
I celebrate the liberation.

1543
00:52:10,513 --> 00:52:11,552
I celebrate the liberation.

1544
00:52:11,553 --> 00:52:12,883
Give me a hint.

1545
00:52:13,023 --> 00:52:15,753
It was an issue that happened while looking at the prompter.

1546
00:52:16,293 --> 00:52:17,593
- I know.
- Yes?

1547
00:52:17,753 --> 00:52:20,462
You have to go through everything while looking at the prompter.

1548
00:52:20,463 --> 00:52:21,592
- Right.
- You got to the place,

1549
00:52:21,593 --> 00:52:22,763
but the prompter was off.

1550
00:52:23,493 --> 00:52:25,433
You have to keep the story going,

1551
00:52:25,703 --> 00:52:28,333
but you've never experienced this.

1552
00:52:29,033 --> 00:52:30,703
So you said, "The prompter is off."

1553
00:52:31,673 --> 00:52:33,003
- Get lost.
- Get lost.

1554
00:52:33,743 --> 00:52:35,773
Get lost.

1555
00:52:35,873 --> 00:52:38,082
- Do you hear Sang Min talk?
- Get lost.

1556
00:52:38,083 --> 00:52:39,312
We'll turn it off for a bit.

1557
00:52:39,313 --> 00:52:40,382
See you next week.

1558
00:52:40,383 --> 00:52:41,452
That's not correct.

1559
00:52:41,453 --> 00:52:43,212
That happens very often.

1560
00:52:43,213 --> 00:52:44,922
- This is so difficult.
- Then how do you solve that?

1561
00:52:44,923 --> 00:52:46,952
It happens often, but we have the script.

1562
00:52:46,953 --> 00:52:48,252
We have the script.

1563
00:52:48,253 --> 00:52:50,092
- Since we have the script, - Do the monitors turn off?

1564
00:52:50,093 --> 00:52:51,222
when the monitors turn off,

1565
00:52:51,223 --> 00:52:52,892
- we just read from the script.
- Right.

1566
00:52:52,893 --> 00:52:54,092
- Like this.
- There are backup plans.

1567
00:52:54,093 --> 00:52:55,832
We have to have backup plans for everything.

1568
00:52:55,833 --> 00:52:56,892
- I know.
- Okay.

1569
00:52:56,893 --> 00:52:58,962
When Dae Ho reads a book,

1570
00:52:58,963 --> 00:53:00,732
he doesn't read horizontally.

1571
00:53:00,733 --> 00:53:02,033
He reads vertically.

1572
00:53:02,773 --> 00:53:05,473
Like "The language of our country is different from that of China?"

1573
00:53:06,643 --> 00:53:08,042
Why don't you get all the hits today?

1574
00:53:08,043 --> 00:53:09,813
Instead of just standing there...

1575
00:53:10,313 --> 00:53:12,042
It's a creative one, though.

1576
00:53:12,043 --> 00:53:13,083
It's not correct.

1577
00:53:13,283 --> 00:53:15,883
There was a typo on the prompter I was reading.

1578
00:53:16,413 --> 00:53:17,953
Because it's human work,

1579
00:53:18,123 --> 00:53:20,753
there may be typos or omissions.

1580
00:53:20,953 --> 00:53:24,023
So the content of the news was delivered completely wrong.

1581
00:53:24,653 --> 00:53:26,122
Let me tell you the original script.

1582
00:53:26,123 --> 00:53:28,132
This was the news.

1583
00:53:28,133 --> 00:53:30,692
Kim Jong Un,

1584
00:53:30,693 --> 00:53:33,303
around 2017,

1585
00:53:33,533 --> 00:53:36,573
once walked out with a limp.

1586
00:53:36,633 --> 00:53:37,932
- It's because of gout.
- I heard...

1587
00:53:37,933 --> 00:53:41,102
- he wasn't well.
- That news kept going out.

1588
00:53:41,103 --> 00:53:42,543
This was the news of that time.

1589
00:53:42,643 --> 00:53:45,312
The North Korean leader...

1590
00:53:45,313 --> 00:53:48,353
walked out with a limp.

1591
00:53:48,553 --> 00:53:53,282
Let's hear what was said at today's Ministry of Unification briefing.

1592
00:53:53,283 --> 00:53:55,722
- Let's hear what was said...
- I expressed...

1593
00:53:55,723 --> 00:53:58,422
something here wrong,

1594
00:53:58,423 --> 00:53:59,822
and that completely changed the meaning.

1595
00:53:59,823 --> 00:54:02,793
Today's Ministry of Gout briefing.

1596
00:54:04,393 --> 00:54:05,462
That's wrong. It's...

1597
00:54:05,463 --> 00:54:07,532
"Let's hear what was said at today's Ministry of Unification briefing."

1598
00:54:07,533 --> 00:54:09,232
The words were all there,

1599
00:54:09,233 --> 00:54:11,642
but there was a missing character.

1600
00:54:11,643 --> 00:54:12,802
- I know!
- Yes!

1601
00:54:12,803 --> 00:54:15,113
Let's hear what was said at today's unification briefing.

1602
00:54:15,913 --> 00:54:17,672
- Reunification happened.
- Today's unification...

1603
00:54:17,673 --> 00:54:18,813
That's strong.

1604
00:54:20,012 --> 00:54:21,612
Is it correct?

1605
00:54:21,953 --> 00:54:24,483
I would have been fired right away if I said that.

1606
00:54:25,283 --> 00:54:26,382
It wasn't that bad.

1607
00:54:26,383 --> 00:54:29,553
With this character omitted, I gave it a nuance.

1608
00:54:29,753 --> 00:54:30,993
- I know.
- Yes?

1609
00:54:31,763 --> 00:54:33,992
Some letters from "today" was missing.

1610
00:54:33,993 --> 00:54:36,863
"Let's hear what was said at, oh, unification briefing."

1611
00:54:37,833 --> 00:54:39,503
Oh, unification briefing.

1612
00:54:39,663 --> 00:54:41,062
I guess it's correct.

1613
00:54:41,063 --> 00:54:42,132
Is it correct?

1614
00:54:42,133 --> 00:54:43,302
- No!
- Kyung Hoon.

1615
00:54:43,303 --> 00:54:44,472
But you're nearly there.

1616
00:54:44,473 --> 00:54:45,702
A character has to be omitted?

1617
00:54:45,703 --> 00:54:46,703
One character.

1618
00:54:46,704 --> 00:54:47,973
The usual unification briefing.

1619
00:54:48,813 --> 00:54:49,843
Correct!

1620
00:54:50,143 --> 00:54:52,012
- What?
- Goodness.

1621
00:54:52,013 --> 00:54:54,142
- It's a mistake.
- That's good.

1622
00:54:54,143 --> 00:54:55,652
- Amazing.
- Missing characters from "today."

1623
00:54:55,653 --> 00:54:57,152
The usual unification briefing.

1624
00:54:57,153 --> 00:54:58,952
- You emphasized the "usual."
- Right.

1625
00:54:58,953 --> 00:55:01,792
"Let's hear what was said at today's unification briefing."

1626
00:55:01,793 --> 00:55:03,693
I tried to give it a feeling.

1627
00:55:04,753 --> 00:55:07,523
"Let's hear what was said at the usual unification briefing."

1628
00:55:09,993 --> 00:55:12,532
It sounds different like that.

1629
00:55:12,533 --> 00:55:13,662
It completely changes the meaning.

1630
00:55:13,663 --> 00:55:14,832
It's totally different.

1631
00:55:14,833 --> 00:55:16,872
- It wasn't usually done.
- That's a mistake.

1632
00:55:16,873 --> 00:55:18,942
It sounded like the Ministry of Unification held briefings...

1633
00:55:18,943 --> 00:55:20,972
all the time.

1634
00:55:20,973 --> 00:55:22,742
- As if they were doing briefings...
- Today and usual...

1635
00:55:22,743 --> 00:55:24,272
- are completely different words.
- about Kim Jong Un.

1636
00:55:24,273 --> 00:55:25,582
You gave it a nuance.

1637
00:55:25,583 --> 00:55:27,682
So I was immediately summoned by the department head.

1638
00:55:27,683 --> 00:55:29,513
You heard the usual scolds that he gave?

1639
00:55:31,453 --> 00:55:32,852
- Right.
- Let's hear...

1640
00:55:32,853 --> 00:55:34,522
the usual scolding.

1641
00:55:34,523 --> 00:55:36,352
When did the Blue House briefing become a usual thing?

1642
00:55:36,353 --> 00:55:38,222
I don't think the viewers noticed that.

1643
00:55:38,223 --> 00:55:40,192
- Right. They don't know.
- It's a bit...

1644
00:55:40,193 --> 00:55:41,222
- They don't know.
- They just move on.

1645
00:55:41,223 --> 00:55:42,693
When we make such mistakes,

1646
00:55:42,963 --> 00:55:44,332
we say, "We're in trouble."

1647
00:55:44,333 --> 00:55:45,502
But it's a mistake only we know.

1648
00:55:45,503 --> 00:55:46,902
Goodness.

1649
00:55:46,903 --> 00:55:48,972
- Kwaktube.
- That happened.

1650
00:55:48,973 --> 00:55:49,973
Kwaktube.

1651
00:55:50,073 --> 00:55:52,703
I'll give you a quiz about a trip I went to.

1652
00:55:52,973 --> 00:55:54,072
I can answer it.

1653
00:55:54,073 --> 00:55:55,842
- This...
- I really can get this.

1654
00:55:55,843 --> 00:55:57,842
is about a country Soo Geun wants to visit the most.

1655
00:55:57,843 --> 00:55:58,843
Where was it?

1656
00:55:58,844 --> 00:56:01,112
When I went to Mexico...

1657
00:56:01,113 --> 00:56:02,152
Mexico.

1658
00:56:02,153 --> 00:56:04,453
It happened when I was traveling by train.

1659
00:56:04,883 --> 00:56:06,382
There's a Mexican train...

1660
00:56:06,383 --> 00:56:08,022
that serves unlimited tequila.

1661
00:56:08,023 --> 00:56:09,222
(A train that serves unlimited tequila)

1662
00:56:09,223 --> 00:56:10,252
There's a tequila train.

1663
00:56:10,253 --> 00:56:12,362
It's a train made...

1664
00:56:12,363 --> 00:56:14,323
by the most famous tequila company.

1665
00:56:14,423 --> 00:56:16,293
When you ride that train, you're given unlimited tequila.

1666
00:56:16,563 --> 00:56:18,933
I asked the waiter for tequila.

1667
00:56:19,333 --> 00:56:21,333
The waiter refused to serve me.

1668
00:56:22,203 --> 00:56:23,602
Why did the waiter refuse? There's a clip.

1669
00:56:23,603 --> 00:56:25,342
It's nice because you have all the clips.

1670
00:56:25,343 --> 00:56:26,673
I have all the videos.

1671
00:56:27,073 --> 00:56:28,513
The train looks so pretty.

1672
00:56:29,113 --> 00:56:31,113
It's the train made by the company.

1673
00:56:31,743 --> 00:56:33,842
(He got on the tequila train.)

1674
00:56:33,843 --> 00:56:36,112
How would the tequila train look?

1675
00:56:36,113 --> 00:56:38,482
(He got on the tequila train.)

1676
00:56:38,483 --> 00:56:40,253
It was made by the company?

1677
00:56:41,253 --> 00:56:43,153
It's like a dining car.

1678
00:56:43,323 --> 00:56:45,162
I really want to go on such a trip.

1679
00:56:45,163 --> 00:56:48,563
A train run by the company that makes tequila.

1680
00:56:49,033 --> 00:56:51,633
(These are all tequila glasses.)

1681
00:56:52,063 --> 00:56:53,863
Salut!

1682
00:56:53,933 --> 00:56:55,373
They're strangers, right?

1683
00:56:58,873 --> 00:57:00,802
(The waiter suddenly looked at the glass and froze.)

1684
00:57:00,803 --> 00:57:02,512
- He's not serving you.
- I asked for a glass.

1685
00:57:02,513 --> 00:57:03,672
He gave the person sitting next to me, but not me.

1686
00:57:03,673 --> 00:57:05,212
I think I can answer it.

1687
00:57:05,213 --> 00:57:06,213
I know.

1688
00:57:06,214 --> 00:57:07,842
- It's not nice to answer so fast.
- I also think...

1689
00:57:07,843 --> 00:57:08,912
- What about it?
- It's...

1690
00:57:08,913 --> 00:57:09,983
Go on, Shin Dong.

1691
00:57:10,583 --> 00:57:11,612
- I think it's the answer.
- Right.

1692
00:57:11,613 --> 00:57:13,983
I think Shin Dong has the answer, so I'll let Jang Hoon say it first.

1693
00:57:14,053 --> 00:57:15,822
Jang Hoon might have the answer.

